233
234WKSelectionDrawingInfo::WKSelectionDrawingInfo()
235 : type(SelectionType::None)
236{
237}
238
239WKSelectionDrawingInfo::WKSelectionDrawingInfo(const EditorState& editorState)
240{
241 if (editorState.selectionIsNone) {
242 type = SelectionType::None;
243 return;
244 }
245
246 if (editorState.isInPlugin) {
247 type = SelectionType::Plugin;
248 return;
249 }
250
251 type = SelectionType::Range;
252 auto& postLayoutData = editorState.postLayoutData();
253 caretRect = postLayoutData.caretRectAtEnd;
254 selectionGeometries = postLayoutData.selectionGeometries;
255 selectionClipRect = postLayoutData.selectionClipRect;
256}
257
258inline bool operator==(const WKSelectionDrawingInfo& a, const WKSelectionDrawingInfo& b)
259{
260 if (a.type != b.type)
261 return false;
262
263 if (a.type == WKSelectionDrawingInfo::SelectionType::Range) {
264 if (a.caretRect != b.caretRect)
265 return false;
266
267 if (a.selectionGeometries.size() != b.selectionGeometries.size())
268 return false;
269
270 for (unsigned i = 0; i < a.selectionGeometries.size(); ++i) {
271 auto& aGeometry = a.selectionGeometries[i];
272 auto& bGeometry = b.selectionGeometries[i];
273 auto behavior = aGeometry.behavior();
274 if (behavior != bGeometry.behavior())
275 return false;
276
277 if (behavior == WebCore::SelectionRenderingBehavior::CoalesceBoundingRects && aGeometry.rect() != bGeometry.rect())
278 return false;
279
280 if (behavior == WebCore::SelectionRenderingBehavior::UseIndividualQuads && aGeometry.quad() != bGeometry.quad())
281 return false;
282 }
283 }
284
285 if (a.type != WKSelectionDrawingInfo::SelectionType::None && a.selectionClipRect != b.selectionClipRect)
286 return false;
287
288 return true;
289}
290
291inline bool operator!=(const WKSelectionDrawingInfo& a, const WKSelectionDrawingInfo& b)
292{
293 return !(a == b);
294}
295
296static TextStream& operator<<(TextStream& stream, WKSelectionDrawingInfo::SelectionType type)
297{
298 switch (type) {
299 case WKSelectionDrawingInfo::SelectionType::None: stream << "none"; break;
300 case WKSelectionDrawingInfo::SelectionType::Plugin: stream << "plugin"; break;
301 case WKSelectionDrawingInfo::SelectionType::Range: stream << "range"; break;
302 }
303
304 return stream;
305}
306
307TextStream& operator<<(TextStream& stream, const WKSelectionDrawingInfo& info)
308{
309 TextStream::GroupScope group(stream);
310 stream.dumpProperty("type", info.type);
311 stream.dumpProperty("caret rect", info.caretRect);
312 stream.dumpProperty("selection geometries", info.selectionGeometries);
313 stream.dumpProperty("selection clip rect", info.selectionClipRect);
314 return stream;
315}

317#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
318
319class ImageAnalysisGestureDeferralToken final : public RefCounted<ImageAnalysisGestureDeferralToken> {
320public:
321 static RefPtr<ImageAnalysisGestureDeferralToken> create(WKContentView *view)
322 {
323 return adoptRef(*new ImageAnalysisGestureDeferralToken(view));
324 }
325
326 ~ImageAnalysisGestureDeferralToken()
327 {
328 if (auto view = m_view.get())
329 [view _endImageAnalysisGestureDeferral:m_shouldPreventTextSelection ? WebKit::ShouldPreventGestures::Yes : WebKit::ShouldPreventGestures::No];
330 }
331
332 void setShouldPreventTextSelection()
333 {
334 m_shouldPreventTextSelection = true;
335 }
336
337private:
338 ImageAnalysisGestureDeferralToken(WKContentView *view)
339 : m_view(view)
340 {
341 }
342
343 WeakObjCPtr<WKContentView> m_view;
344 bool m_shouldPreventTextSelection { false };
345};
346
347#endif // ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)

425@implementation WKFormInputSession {
426 WeakObjCPtr<WKContentView> _contentView;
427 RetainPtr<WKFocusedElementInfo> _focusedElementInfo;
428 RetainPtr<UIView> _customInputView;
429 RetainPtr<UIView> _customInputAccessoryView;
430 RetainPtr<NSArray<UITextSuggestion *>> _suggestions;
431 BOOL _accessoryViewShouldNotShow;
432 BOOL _forceSecureTextEntry;
433 BOOL _requiresStrongPasswordAssistance;
434}
435
436- (instancetype)initWithContentView:(WKContentView *)view focusedElementInfo:(WKFocusedElementInfo *)elementInfo requiresStrongPasswordAssistance:(BOOL)requiresStrongPasswordAssistance
437{
438 if (!(self = [super init]))
439 return nil;
440
441 _contentView = view;
442 _focusedElementInfo = elementInfo;
443 _requiresStrongPasswordAssistance = requiresStrongPasswordAssistance;
444
445 return self;
446}
447
448- (id <_WKFocusedElementInfo>)focusedElementInfo
449{
450 return _focusedElementInfo.get();
451}
452
453- (NSObject <NSSecureCoding> *)userObject
454{
455 return [_focusedElementInfo userObject];
456}
457
458- (BOOL)isValid
459{
460 return !!_contentView;
461}
462
463- (NSString *)accessoryViewCustomButtonTitle
464{
465 return [[[_contentView formAccessoryView] _autofill] title];
466}
467
468- (void)setAccessoryViewCustomButtonTitle:(NSString *)title
469{
470 if (title.length)
471 [[_contentView formAccessoryView] showAutoFillButtonWithTitle:title];
472 else
473 [[_contentView formAccessoryView] hideAutoFillButton];
474 if (WebKit::currentUserInterfaceIdiomIsPadOrMac())
475 [_contentView reloadInputViews];
476}
477
478- (BOOL)accessoryViewShouldNotShow
479{
480 return _accessoryViewShouldNotShow;
481}
482
483- (void)setAccessoryViewShouldNotShow:(BOOL)accessoryViewShouldNotShow
484{
485 if (_accessoryViewShouldNotShow == accessoryViewShouldNotShow)
486 return;
487
488 _accessoryViewShouldNotShow = accessoryViewShouldNotShow;
489 [_contentView reloadInputViews];
490}
491
492- (BOOL)forceSecureTextEntry
493{
494 return _forceSecureTextEntry;
495}
496
497- (void)setForceSecureTextEntry:(BOOL)forceSecureTextEntry
498{
499 if (_forceSecureTextEntry == forceSecureTextEntry)
500 return;
501
502 _forceSecureTextEntry = forceSecureTextEntry;
503 [_contentView reloadInputViews];
504}
505
506- (UIView *)customInputView
507{
508 return _customInputView.get();
509}
510
511- (void)setCustomInputView:(UIView *)customInputView
512{
513 if (customInputView == _customInputView)
514 return;
515
516 _customInputView = customInputView;
517 [_contentView reloadInputViews];
518}
519
520- (UIView *)customInputAccessoryView
521{
522 return _customInputAccessoryView.get();
523}
524
525- (void)setCustomInputAccessoryView:(UIView *)customInputAccessoryView
526{
527 if (_customInputAccessoryView == customInputAccessoryView)
528 return;
529
530 _customInputAccessoryView = customInputAccessoryView;
531 [_contentView reloadInputViews];
532}
533
534- (void)endEditing
535{
536 if ([_customInputView conformsToProtocol:@protocol(WKFormControl)])
537 [(id<WKFormControl>)_customInputView.get() controlEndEditing];
538}
539
540- (NSArray<UITextSuggestion *> *)suggestions
541{
542 return _suggestions.get();
543}
544
545- (void)setSuggestions:(NSArray<UITextSuggestion *> *)suggestions
546{
547 if (suggestions == _suggestions || [suggestions isEqualToArray:_suggestions.get()])
548 return;
549
550 _suggestions = adoptNS([suggestions copy]);
551 [_contentView updateTextSuggestionsForInputDelegate];
552}
553
554- (BOOL)requiresStrongPasswordAssistance
555{
556 return _requiresStrongPasswordAssistance;
557}
558
559- (void)invalidate
560{
561 id <UITextInputSuggestionDelegate> suggestionDelegate = (id <UITextInputSuggestionDelegate>)[_contentView inputDelegate];
562 [suggestionDelegate setSuggestions:nil];
563 _contentView = nil;
564}
565
566- (void)reloadFocusedElementContextView
567{
568 [_contentView reloadContextViewForPresentedListViewController];
569}

573@implementation WKFocusedElementInfo {
574 WKInputType _type;
575 RetainPtr<NSString> _value;
576 BOOL _isUserInitiated;
577 RetainPtr<NSObject <NSSecureCoding>> _userObject;
578 RetainPtr<NSString> _placeholder;
579 RetainPtr<NSString> _label;
580}
581
582- (instancetype)initWithFocusedElementInformation:(const WebKit::FocusedElementInformation&)information isUserInitiated:(BOOL)isUserInitiated userObject:(NSObject <NSSecureCoding> *)userObject
583{
584 if (!(self = [super init]))
585 return nil;
586
587 switch (information.elementType) {
588 case WebKit::InputType::ContentEditable:
589 _type = WKInputTypeContentEditable;
590 break;
591 case WebKit::InputType::Text:
592 _type = WKInputTypeText;
593 break;
594 case WebKit::InputType::Password:
595 _type = WKInputTypePassword;
596 break;
597 case WebKit::InputType::TextArea:
598 _type = WKInputTypeTextArea;
599 break;
600 case WebKit::InputType::Search:
601 _type = WKInputTypeSearch;
602 break;
603 case WebKit::InputType::Email:
604 _type = WKInputTypeEmail;
605 break;
606 case WebKit::InputType::URL:
607 _type = WKInputTypeURL;
608 break;
609 case WebKit::InputType::Phone:
610 _type = WKInputTypePhone;
611 break;
612 case WebKit::InputType::Number:
613 _type = WKInputTypeNumber;
614 break;
615 case WebKit::InputType::NumberPad:
616 _type = WKInputTypeNumberPad;
617 break;
618 case WebKit::InputType::Date:
619 _type = WKInputTypeDate;
620 break;
621 case WebKit::InputType::DateTimeLocal:
622 _type = WKInputTypeDateTimeLocal;
623 break;
624 case WebKit::InputType::Month:
625 _type = WKInputTypeMonth;
626 break;
627 case WebKit::InputType::Week:
628 _type = WKInputTypeWeek;
629 break;
630 case WebKit::InputType::Time:
631 _type = WKInputTypeTime;
632 break;
633 case WebKit::InputType::Select:
634 _type = WKInputTypeSelect;
635 break;
636 case WebKit::InputType::Drawing:
637 _type = WKInputTypeDrawing;
638 break;
639#if ENABLE(INPUT_TYPE_COLOR)
640 case WebKit::InputType::Color:
641 _type = WKInputTypeColor;
642 break;
643#endif
644 case WebKit::InputType::None:
645 _type = WKInputTypeNone;
646 break;
647 }
648 _value = information.value;
649 _isUserInitiated = isUserInitiated;
650 _userObject = userObject;
651 _placeholder = information.placeholder;
652 _label = information.label;
653 return self;
654}
655
656- (WKInputType)type
657{
658 return _type;
659}
660
661- (NSString *)value
662{
663 return _value.get();
664}
665
666- (BOOL)isUserInitiated
667{
668 return _isUserInitiated;
669}
670
671- (NSObject <NSSecureCoding> *)userObject
672{
673 return _userObject.get();
674}
675
676- (NSString *)label
677{
678 return _label.get();
679}
680
681- (NSString *)placeholder
682{
683 return _placeholder.get();
684}

688#if ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)
689
690@interface WKDragSessionContext : NSObject
691- (void)addTemporaryDirectory:(NSString *)temporaryDirectory;
692- (void)cleanUpTemporaryDirectories;
693@end
694
695@implementation WKDragSessionContext {
696 RetainPtr<NSMutableArray> _temporaryDirectories;
697}
698
699- (void)addTemporaryDirectory:(NSString *)temporaryDirectory
700{
701 if (!_temporaryDirectories)
702 _temporaryDirectories = adoptNS([NSMutableArray new]);
703 [_temporaryDirectories addObject:temporaryDirectory];
704}
705
706- (void)cleanUpTemporaryDirectories
707{
708 for (NSString *directory in _temporaryDirectories.get()) {
709 NSError *error = nil;
710 [[NSFileManager defaultManager] removeItemAtPath:directory error:&error];
711 RELEASE_LOG(DragAndDrop, "Removed temporary download directory: %@ with error: %@", directory, error);
712 }
713 _temporaryDirectories = nil;
714}
715
716@end
717
718static WKDragSessionContext *existingLocalDragSessionContext(id <UIDragSession> session)
719{
720 return [session.localContext isKindOfClass:[WKDragSessionContext class]] ? (WKDragSessionContext *)session.localContext : nil;
721}
722
723static WKDragSessionContext *ensureLocalDragSessionContext(id <UIDragSession> session)
724{
725 if (WKDragSessionContext *existingContext = existingLocalDragSessionContext(session))
726 return existingContext;
727
728 if (session.localContext) {
729 RELEASE_LOG(DragAndDrop, "Overriding existing local context: %@ on session: %@", session.localContext, session);
730 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
731 }
732
733 session.localContext = adoptNS([[WKDragSessionContext alloc] init]).get();
734 return (WKDragSessionContext *)session.localContext;
735}

737#endif // ENABLE(DRAG_SUPPORT)

750- (BOOL)_wk_isTapAndAHalf
751{
752 static dispatch_once_t onceToken;
753 static Class tapAndAHalfGestureRecognizerClass;
754 dispatch_once(&onceToken, ^{
755 tapAndAHalfGestureRecognizerClass = NSClassFromString(@"UITapAndAHalfRecognizer");
756 });
757 return [self isKindOfClass:tapAndAHalfGestureRecognizerClass];
758}

785- (void)_createAndConfigureDoubleTapGestureRecognizer
786{
787 if (_doubleTapGestureRecognizer) {
788 [self removeGestureRecognizer:_doubleTapGestureRecognizer.get()];
789 [_doubleTapGestureRecognizer setDelegate:nil];
790 [_doubleTapGestureRecognizer setGestureFailedTarget:nil action:nil];
791 }
792
793 _doubleTapGestureRecognizer = adoptNS([[WKSyntheticTapGestureRecognizer alloc] initWithTarget:self action:@selector(_doubleTapRecognized:)]);
794 [_doubleTapGestureRecognizer setGestureFailedTarget:self action:@selector(_doubleTapDidFail:)];
795 [_doubleTapGestureRecognizer setNumberOfTapsRequired:2];
796 [_doubleTapGestureRecognizer setDelegate:self];
797 [self addGestureRecognizer:_doubleTapGestureRecognizer.get()];
798 [_singleTapGestureRecognizer requireGestureRecognizerToFail:_doubleTapGestureRecognizer.get()];
799}

801- (void)_createAndConfigureLongPressGestureRecognizer
802{
803 _longPressGestureRecognizer = adoptNS([[UILongPressGestureRecognizer alloc] initWithTarget:self action:@selector(_longPressRecognized:)]);
804 [_longPressGestureRecognizer setDelay:tapAndHoldDelay];
805 [_longPressGestureRecognizer setDelegate:self];
806 [_longPressGestureRecognizer _setRequiresQuietImpulse:YES];
807 [self addGestureRecognizer:_longPressGestureRecognizer.get()];
808}

810- (void)setUpInteraction
811{
812 // If the page is not valid yet then delay interaction setup until the process is launched/relaunched.
813 if (!_page->hasRunningProcess())
814 return;
815
816 if (_hasSetUpInteractions)
817 return;
818
819 if (!_interactionViewsContainerView) {
820 _interactionViewsContainerView = adoptNS([[UIView alloc] init]);
821 [_interactionViewsContainerView layer].name = @"InteractionViewsContainer";
822 [_interactionViewsContainerView setOpaque:NO];
823 [_interactionViewsContainerView layer].anchorPoint = CGPointZero;

825 }
826

830 [self.layer addObserver:self forKeyPath:@"transform" options:NSKeyValueObservingOptionInitial context:WKContentViewKVOTransformContext];
831

835 [self addGestureRecognizer:_touchActionLeftSwipeGestureRecognizer.get()];

840 [self addGestureRecognizer:_touchActionRightSwipeGestureRecognizer.get()];

845 [self addGestureRecognizer:_touchActionUpSwipeGestureRecognizer.get()];
846

848 [_touchActionDownSwipeGestureRecognizer setDirection:UISwipeGestureRecognizerDirectionDown];

1202- (void)_cancelPendingKeyEventHandler
1203{
1204 if (!_page)
1205 return;
1206
1207 ASSERT_IMPLIES(_keyWebEventHandler, _page->hasQueuedKeyEvent());
1208 if (!_page->hasQueuedKeyEvent())
1209 return;
1210
1211 if (auto keyEventHandler = std::exchange(_keyWebEventHandler, nil))
1212 keyEventHandler(_page->firstQueuedKeyEvent().nativeEvent(), NO);
1213}

1276- (void)_updateLongPressAndHighlightLongPressGestures
1277{
1278 // We only disable the highlight long press gesture in the case where UIContextMenu is available and we
1279 // also allow link previews, since the context menu interaction's gestures need to take precedence over
1280 // highlight long press gestures.
1281 [_highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer setEnabled:!self._shouldUseContextMenus || !self.webView.allowsLinkPreview];
1282
1283 // We only enable the long press gesture in the case where the app is linked on iOS 12 or earlier (and
1284 // therefore prefers the legacy action sheet over context menus), and link previews are also enabled.
1285 [_longPressGestureRecognizer setEnabled:!self._shouldUseContextMenus && self.webView.allowsLinkPreview];
1286}

1326- (void)observeValueForKeyPath:(NSString *)keyPath ofObject:(id)object change:(NSDictionary *)change context:(void *)context
1327{
1328 if (context != WKContentViewKVOTransformContext) {
1329 [super observeValueForKeyPath:keyPath ofObject:object change:change context:context];
1330 return;
1331 }
1332
1333 ASSERT([keyPath isEqualToString:@"transform"]);
1334 ASSERT(object == self.layer);
1335
1336 if ([UIView _isInAnimationBlock] && _page->editorState().selectionIsNone) {
1337 // If the utility views are not already visible, we don't want them to become visible during the animation since
1338 // they could not start from a reasonable state.
1339 // This is not perfect since views could also get updated during the animation, in practice this is rare and the end state
1340 // remains correct.
1341 [self _cancelInteraction];
1342 [_interactionViewsContainerView setHidden:YES];
1343 [UIView _addCompletion:^(BOOL){ [_interactionViewsContainerView setHidden:NO]; }];
1344 }
1345
1346 [self _updateTapHighlight];
1347
1348 _selectionNeedsUpdate = YES;
1349 [self _updateChangedSelection:YES];
1350}

1372- (UIView *)hitTest:(CGPoint)point withEvent:(::UIEvent *)event
1373{
1374 for (UIView *subView in [_interactionViewsContainerView.get() subviews]) {
1375 UIView *hitView = [subView hitTest:[subView convertPoint:point fromView:self] withEvent:event];
1376 if (hitView) {
1377 LOG_WITH_STREAM(UIHitTesting, stream << self << "hitTest at " << WebCore::FloatPoint(point) << " found interaction view " << hitView);
1378 return hitView;
1379 }
1380 }
1381
1382 LOG_WITH_STREAM(UIHitTesting, stream << "hit-testing WKContentView subviews " << [[self recursiveDescription] UTF8String]);
1383 UIView* hitView = [super hitTest:point withEvent:event];
1384 LOG_WITH_STREAM(UIHitTesting, stream << " found view " << [hitView class] << " " << (void*)hitView);
1385 return hitView;
1386}

1473- (BOOL)becomeFirstResponder

1478- (BOOL)becomeFirstResponderForWebView
1479{
1480 if (_resigningFirstResponder)
1481 return NO;
1482
1483 if (!_inputViewUpdateDeferrer)
1484 _inputViewUpdateDeferrer = makeUnique<WebKit::InputViewUpdateDeferrer>(self);
1485
1486 BOOL didBecomeFirstResponder;
1487 {
1488 SetForScope<BOOL> becomingFirstResponder { _becomingFirstResponder, YES };
1489 didBecomeFirstResponder = [super becomeFirstResponder];
1490 }
1491
1492 if (didBecomeFirstResponder) {
1493 _page->installActivityStateChangeCompletionHandler([weakSelf = WeakObjCPtr<WKContentView>(self)] {
1494 if (!weakSelf)
1495 return;
1496
1497 auto strongSelf = weakSelf.get();
1498 [strongSelf _resetInputViewDeferral];
1499 });
1500
1501 _page->activityStateDidChange(WebCore::ActivityState::IsFocused, WebKit::WebPageProxy::ActivityStateChangeDispatchMode::Immediate);
1502
1503 if ([self canShowNonEmptySelectionView] || (!_suppressSelectionAssistantReasons && _activeTextInteractionCount))
1504 [_textInteractionAssistant activateSelection];
1505
1506 [self _scheduleResetInputViewDeferralAfterBecomingFirstResponder];
1507 } else
1508 [self _resetInputViewDeferral];
1509
1510 return didBecomeFirstResponder;
1511}

1513- (BOOL)resignFirstResponder
1514{
1515 return [_webView resignFirstResponder];
1516}
1517
1518typedef NS_ENUM(NSInteger, EndEditingReason) {
1519 EndEditingReasonAccessoryDone,
1520 EndEditingReasonResigningFirstResponder,
1521};
1522
1523- (void)endEditingAndUpdateFocusAppearanceWithReason:(EndEditingReason)reason
1524{
1525 if (!self.webView._retainingActiveFocusedState) {
1526 // We need to complete the editing operation before we blur the element.
1527 [self _endEditing];
1528
1529 auto shouldBlurFocusedElement = [&] {
1530 if (_keyboardDidRequestDismissal)
1531 return true;
1532
1533 if (self._shouldUseLegacySelectPopoverDismissalBehavior)
1534 return true;
1535
1536 if (reason == EndEditingReasonAccessoryDone) {
1537 if (_focusRequiresStrongPasswordAssistance)
1538 return true;
1539
1540 if (!WebKit::currentUserInterfaceIdiomIsPadOrMac())
1541 return true;
1542 }
1543
1544 return false;
1545 };
1546
1547 if (shouldBlurFocusedElement()) {
1548 _page->blurFocusedElement();
1549 // Don't wait for WebPageProxy::blurFocusedElement() to round-trip back to us to hide the keyboard
1550 // because we know that the user explicitly requested us to do so.
1551 [self _elementDidBlur];
1552 }
1553 }
1554
1555 [self _cancelInteraction];
1556 [_textInteractionAssistant deactivateSelection];
1557
1558 [self _resetInputViewDeferral];
1559}
1560
1561- (BOOL)resignFirstResponderForWebView
1562{
1563 // FIXME: Maybe we should call resignFirstResponder on the superclass
1564 // and do nothing if the return value is NO.
1565
1566 SetForScope<BOOL> resigningFirstResponderScope { _resigningFirstResponder, YES };
1567
1568 [self endEditingAndUpdateFocusAppearanceWithReason:EndEditingReasonResigningFirstResponder];
1569
1570 // If the user explicitly dismissed the keyboard then we will lose first responder
1571 // status only to gain it back again. Just don't resign in that case.
1572 if (_keyboardDidRequestDismissal) {
1573 _keyboardDidRequestDismissal = NO;
1574 return NO;
1575 }
1576
1577 bool superDidResign = [super resignFirstResponder];
1578
1579 if (superDidResign) {
1580 [self _handleDOMPasteRequestWithResult:WebCore::DOMPasteAccessResponse::DeniedForGesture];
1581 _page->activityStateDidChange(WebCore::ActivityState::IsFocused, WebKit::WebPageProxy::ActivityStateChangeDispatchMode::Immediate);
1582
1583 if (_keyWebEventHandler) {
1584 RunLoop::main().dispatch([weakHandler = WeakObjCPtr<id>(_keyWebEventHandler.get()), weakSelf = WeakObjCPtr<WKContentView>(self)] {
1585 auto strongSelf = weakSelf.get();
1586 if (!strongSelf || [strongSelf isFirstResponder])
1587 return;
1588 auto strongHandler = weakHandler.get();
1589 if (!strongHandler)
1590 return;
1591 if (strongSelf->_keyWebEventHandler.get() != strongHandler.get())
1592 return;
1593 auto keyEventHandler = std::exchange(strongSelf->_keyWebEventHandler, nil);
1594 auto page = strongSelf->_page;
1595 if (!page)
1596 return;
1597 if (!page->hasQueuedKeyEvent())
1598 return;
1599 keyEventHandler(page->firstQueuedKeyEvent().nativeEvent(), YES);
1600 });
1601 }
1602 }
1603
1604 return superDidResign;
1605}

1607- (void)cancelPointersForGestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
1608{
1609 NSMapTable<NSNumber *, UITouch *> *activeTouches = [_touchEventGestureRecognizer activeTouchesByIdentifier];
1610 for (NSNumber *touchIdentifier in activeTouches) {
1611 UITouch *touch = [activeTouches objectForKey:touchIdentifier];
1612 if ([touch.gestureRecognizers containsObject:gestureRecognizer])
1613 _page->cancelPointer([touchIdentifier unsignedIntValue], WebCore::roundedIntPoint([touch locationInView:self]));
1614 }
1615}

1617- (std::optional<unsigned>)activeTouchIdentifierForGestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
1618{
1619 NSMapTable<NSNumber *, UITouch *> *activeTouches = [_touchEventGestureRecognizer activeTouchesByIdentifier];
1620 for (NSNumber *touchIdentifier in activeTouches) {
1621 UITouch *touch = [activeTouches objectForKey:touchIdentifier];
1622 if ([touch.gestureRecognizers containsObject:gestureRecognizer])
1623 return [touchIdentifier unsignedIntValue];
1624 }
1625 return std::nullopt;
1626}

1632#else

1634#endif

1637- (BOOL)_touchEventsMustRequireGestureRecognizerToFail:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
1638{
1639 auto webView = self.webView;
1640 if ([webView _isNavigationSwipeGestureRecognizer:gestureRecognizer])
1641 return YES;
1642
1643 id <WKUIDelegatePrivate> uiDelegate = static_cast<id <WKUIDelegatePrivate>>([webView UIDelegate]);
1644 return gestureRecognizer.view == webView && [uiDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:touchEventsMustRequireGestureRecognizerToFail:)]
1645 && [uiDelegate _webView:webView touchEventsMustRequireGestureRecognizerToFail:gestureRecognizer];
1646}
1647
1648- (void)_webTouchEventsRecognized:(UIWebTouchEventsGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
1649{
1650 if (!_page->hasRunningProcess())
1651 return;
1652
1653 const _UIWebTouchEvent* lastTouchEvent = gestureRecognizer.lastTouchEvent;
1654
1655 _lastInteractionLocation = lastTouchEvent->locationInDocumentCoordinates;
1656 if (lastTouchEvent->type == UIWebTouchEventTouchBegin) {
1657 [self _handleDOMPasteRequestWithResult:WebCore::DOMPasteAccessResponse::DeniedForGesture];
1658 _layerTreeTransactionIdAtLastInteractionStart = downcast<WebKit::RemoteLayerTreeDrawingAreaProxy>(*_page->drawingArea()).lastCommittedLayerTreeTransactionID();
1659
1660#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
1661 _page->resetPotentialTapSecurityOrigin();
1662#endif
1663
1664 WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest positionInformationRequest { WebCore::IntPoint(_lastInteractionLocation) };
1665 [self doAfterPositionInformationUpdate:[assistant = WeakObjCPtr<WKActionSheetAssistant>(_actionSheetAssistant.get())] (WebKit::InteractionInformationAtPosition information) {
1666 [assistant interactionDidStartWithPositionInformation:information];
1667 } forRequest:positionInformationRequest];
1668 }
1669
1670#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
1671 WebKit::NativeWebTouchEvent nativeWebTouchEvent { lastTouchEvent, gestureRecognizerModifierFlags(gestureRecognizer) };
1672 nativeWebTouchEvent.setCanPreventNativeGestures(_touchEventsCanPreventNativeGestures || [gestureRecognizer isDefaultPrevented]);
1673
1674 [self _handleTouchActionsForTouchEvent:nativeWebTouchEvent];
1675
1676 if (_touchEventsCanPreventNativeGestures)
1677 _page->handlePreventableTouchEvent(nativeWebTouchEvent);
1678 else
1679 _page->handleUnpreventableTouchEvent(nativeWebTouchEvent);
1680
1681 if (nativeWebTouchEvent.allTouchPointsAreReleased()) {
1682 _touchEventsCanPreventNativeGestures = YES;
1683
1684 if (!_page->isScrollingOrZooming())
1685 [self _resetPanningPreventionFlags];
1686
1687 if (nativeWebTouchEvent.isPotentialTap() && self.hasHiddenContentEditable && self._hasFocusedElement && !self.window.keyWindow)
1688 [self.window makeKeyWindow];
1689
1690 auto stopDeferringNativeGesturesIfNeeded = [] (NSArray<WKDeferringGestureRecognizer *> *deferringGestures) {
1691 for (WKDeferringGestureRecognizer *gesture in deferringGestures) {
1692 if (gesture.state == UIGestureRecognizerStatePossible)
1693 gesture.state = UIGestureRecognizerStateFailed;
1694 }
1695 };
1696
1697 if (!_page->isHandlingPreventableTouchStart())
1698 stopDeferringNativeGesturesIfNeeded(self._touchStartDeferringGestures);
1699
1700 if (!_page->isHandlingPreventableTouchEnd())
1701 stopDeferringNativeGesturesIfNeeded(self._touchEndDeferringGestures);
1702 }
1703#endif // ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
1704}
1705
1706#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
1707- (void)_handleTouchActionsForTouchEvent:(const WebKit::NativeWebTouchEvent&)touchEvent
1708{
1709 auto* scrollingCoordinator = _page->scrollingCoordinatorProxy();
1710 if (!scrollingCoordinator)
1711 return;
1712
1713 for (const auto& touchPoint : touchEvent.touchPoints()) {
1714 auto phase = touchPoint.phase();
1715 if (phase == WebKit::WebPlatformTouchPoint::TouchPressed) {
1716 auto touchActions = WebKit::touchActionsForPoint(self, touchPoint.location());
1717 LOG_WITH_STREAM(UIHitTesting, stream << "touchActionsForPoint " << touchPoint.location() << " found " << touchActions);
1718 if (!touchActions || touchActions.contains(WebCore::TouchAction::Auto))
1719 continue;
1720 [_touchActionGestureRecognizer setTouchActions:touchActions forTouchIdentifier:touchPoint.identifier()];
1721 scrollingCoordinator->setTouchActionsForTouchIdentifier(touchActions, touchPoint.identifier());
1722 _preventsPanningInXAxis = !touchActions.containsAny({ WebCore::TouchAction::PanX, WebCore::TouchAction::Manipulation });
1723 _preventsPanningInYAxis = !touchActions.containsAny({ WebCore::TouchAction::PanY, WebCore::TouchAction::Manipulation });
1724 } else if (phase == WebKit::WebPlatformTouchPoint::TouchReleased || phase == WebKit::WebPlatformTouchPoint::TouchCancelled) {
1725 [_touchActionGestureRecognizer clearTouchActionsForTouchIdentifier:touchPoint.identifier()];
1726 scrollingCoordinator->clearTouchActionsForTouchIdentifier(touchPoint.identifier());
1727 }
1728 }
1729}
1730#endif // ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
1731
1732- (BOOL)gestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer shouldReceiveTouch:(UITouch *)touch
1733{
1734#if HAVE(LOOKUP_GESTURE_RECOGNIZER)
1735 if (gestureRecognizer == _lookupGestureRecognizer)
1736 return YES;
1737#endif
1738
1739#if ENABLE(HOVER_GESTURE_RECOGNIZER)
1740 if (gestureRecognizer == _hoverGestureRecognizer)
1741 return NO;
1742#endif
1743
1744#if HAVE(UIKIT_WITH_MOUSE_SUPPORT)
1745 if (gestureRecognizer != _mouseGestureRecognizer && [_mouseGestureRecognizer mouseTouch] == touch)
1746 return NO;
1747
1748 if (gestureRecognizer == _mouseGestureRecognizer)
1749 return [_mouseGestureRecognizer mouseTouch] == touch;
1750
1751 if (gestureRecognizer == _doubleTapGestureRecognizer || gestureRecognizer == _nonBlockingDoubleTapGestureRecognizer)
1752 return touch.type != UITouchTypeIndirectPointer;
1753#endif
1754
1755 if (gestureRecognizer == _touchActionLeftSwipeGestureRecognizer || gestureRecognizer == _touchActionRightSwipeGestureRecognizer || gestureRecognizer == _touchActionUpSwipeGestureRecognizer || gestureRecognizer == _touchActionDownSwipeGestureRecognizer) {
1756 // We update the enabled state of the various swipe gesture recognizers such that if we have a unidirectional touch-action
1757 // specified (only pan-x or only pan-y) we enable the two recognizers in the opposite axis to prevent scrolling from starting
1758 // if the initial gesture is such a swipe. Since the recognizers are specified to use a single finger for recognition, we don't
1759 // need to worry about the case where there may be more than a single touch for a given UIScrollView.
1760 auto touchLocation = [touch locationInView:self];
1761 auto touchActions = WebKit::touchActionsForPoint(self, WebCore::roundedIntPoint(touchLocation));
1762 LOG_WITH_STREAM(UIHitTesting, stream << "gestureRecognizer:shouldReceiveTouch: at " << WebCore::FloatPoint(touchLocation) << " - touch actions " << touchActions);
1763 if (gestureRecognizer == _touchActionLeftSwipeGestureRecognizer || gestureRecognizer == _touchActionRightSwipeGestureRecognizer)
1764 return touchActions == WebCore::TouchAction::PanY;
1765 return touchActions == WebCore::TouchAction::PanX;
1766 }
1767
1768 return YES;
1769}
1770
1771- (BOOL)gestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer shouldReceivePress:(UIPress *)press
1772{
1773#if HAVE(UIKIT_WITH_MOUSE_SUPPORT)
1774 if (gestureRecognizer == _mouseGestureRecognizer)
1775 return NO;
1776#endif
1777#if ENABLE(HOVER_GESTURE_RECOGNIZER)
1778 if (gestureRecognizer == _hoverGestureRecognizer)
1779 return NO;
1780#endif
1781 return YES;
1782}
1783
1784#pragma mark - WKTouchActionGestureRecognizerDelegate implementation
1785
1786- (BOOL)gestureRecognizerMayPanWebView:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
1787{
1788 // The gesture recognizer is the main UIScrollView's UIPanGestureRecognizer.
1789 if (gestureRecognizer == [_webView scrollView].panGestureRecognizer)
1790 return YES;
1791
1792 // The gesture recognizer is a child UIScrollView's UIPanGestureRecognizer created by WebKit.
1793 if (gestureRecognizer.view && [gestureRecognizer.view isKindOfClass:[WKChildScrollView class]])
1794 return YES;
1795
1796 return NO;
1797}
1798
1799- (BOOL)gestureRecognizerMayPinchToZoomWebView:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
1800{
1801 // The gesture recognizer is the main UIScrollView's UIPinchGestureRecognizer.
1802 if (gestureRecognizer == [_webView scrollView].pinchGestureRecognizer)
1803 return YES;
1804
1805 // The gesture recognizer is another UIPichGestureRecognizer known to lead to pinch-to-zoom.
1806 if ([gestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:[UIPinchGestureRecognizer class]]) {
1807 if (auto uiDelegate = static_cast<id<WKUIDelegatePrivate>>(self.webView.UIDelegate)) {
1808 if ([uiDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:gestureRecognizerCouldPinch:)])
1809 return [uiDelegate _webView:self.webView gestureRecognizerCouldPinch:gestureRecognizer];
1810 }
1811 }
1812 return NO;
1813}
1814
1815- (BOOL)gestureRecognizerMayDoubleTapToZoomWebView:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
1816{
1817 return gestureRecognizer == _doubleTapGestureRecognizer || gestureRecognizer == _twoFingerDoubleTapGestureRecognizer;
1818}

1825- (void)_resetPanningPreventionFlags
1826{
1827 _preventsPanningInXAxis = NO;
1828 _preventsPanningInYAxis = NO;
1829}
1830
1831- (void)_inspectorNodeSearchRecognized:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
1832{
1833 ASSERT(_inspectorNodeSearchEnabled);
1834 [self _resetIsDoubleTapPending];
1835
1836 CGPoint point = [gestureRecognizer locationInView:self];
1837
1838 switch (gestureRecognizer.state) {
1839 case UIGestureRecognizerStateBegan:
1840 case UIGestureRecognizerStateChanged:
1841 _page->inspectorNodeSearchMovedToPosition(point);
1842 break;
1843 case UIGestureRecognizerStateEnded:
1844 case UIGestureRecognizerStateCancelled:
1845 default: // To ensure we turn off node search.
1846 _page->inspectorNodeSearchEndedAtPosition(point);
1847 break;
1848 }
1849}
1850
1851static WebCore::FloatQuad inflateQuad(const WebCore::FloatQuad& quad, float inflateSize)
1852{
1853 // We sort the output points like this (as expected by the highlight view):
1854 // p2------p3
1855 // | |
1856 // p1------p4
1857
1858 // 1) Sort the points horizontally.
1859 WebCore::FloatPoint points[4] = { quad.p1(), quad.p4(), quad.p2(), quad.p3() };
1860 if (points[0].x() > points[1].x())
1861 std::swap(points[0], points[1]);
1862 if (points[2].x() > points[3].x())
1863 std::swap(points[2], points[3]);
1864
1865 if (points[0].x() > points[2].x())
1866 std::swap(points[0], points[2]);
1867 if (points[1].x() > points[3].x())
1868 std::swap(points[1], points[3]);
1869
1870 if (points[1].x() > points[2].x())
1871 std::swap(points[1], points[2]);
1872
1873 // 2) Swap them vertically to have the output points [p2, p1, p3, p4].
1874 if (points[1].y() < points[0].y())
1875 std::swap(points[0], points[1]);
1876 if (points[3].y() < points[2].y())
1877 std::swap(points[2], points[3]);
1878
1879 // 3) Adjust the positions.
1880 points[0].move(-inflateSize, -inflateSize);
1881 points[1].move(-inflateSize, inflateSize);
1882 points[2].move(inflateSize, -inflateSize);
1883 points[3].move(inflateSize, inflateSize);
1884
1885 return WebCore::FloatQuad(points[1], points[0], points[2], points[3]);
1886}
1887
1888#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
1889- (void)_webTouchEvent:(const WebKit::NativeWebTouchEvent&)touchEvent preventsNativeGestures:(BOOL)preventsNativeGesture
1890{
1891 if (!preventsNativeGesture || ![_touchEventGestureRecognizer isDispatchingTouchEvents])
1892 return;
1893
1894 _longPressCanClick = NO;
1895 _touchEventsCanPreventNativeGestures = NO;
1896 [_touchEventGestureRecognizer setDefaultPrevented:YES];
1897}
1898#endif

1913- (NSArray<WKDeferringGestureRecognizer *> *)deferringGestures
1914{
1915 auto gestures = [NSMutableArray arrayWithCapacity:7];
1916 [gestures addObjectsFromArray:self._touchStartDeferringGestures];
1917 [gestures addObjectsFromArray:self._touchEndDeferringGestures];
1918#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
1919 [gestures addObject:_imageAnalysisDeferringGestureRecognizer.get()];
1920#endif
1921 return gestures;
1922}

1924- (NSArray<WKDeferringGestureRecognizer *> *)_touchStartDeferringGestures
1925{
1926 WKDeferringGestureRecognizer *recognizers[3];
1927 NSUInteger count = 0;
1928 auto add = [&] (const RetainPtr<WKDeferringGestureRecognizer>& recognizer) {
1929 if (recognizer)
1930 recognizers[count++] = recognizer.get();
1931 };
1932 add(_touchStartDeferringGestureRecognizerForImmediatelyResettableGestures);
1933 add(_touchStartDeferringGestureRecognizerForDelayedResettableGestures);
1934 add(_touchStartDeferringGestureRecognizerForSyntheticTapGestures);
1935 return [NSArray arrayWithObjects:recognizers count:count];
1936}
1937
1938- (NSArray<WKDeferringGestureRecognizer *> *)_touchEndDeferringGestures
1939{
1940 WKDeferringGestureRecognizer *recognizers[3];
1941 NSUInteger count = 0;
1942 auto add = [&] (const RetainPtr<WKDeferringGestureRecognizer>& recognizer) {
1943 if (recognizer)
1944 recognizers[count++] = recognizer.get();
1945 };
1946 add(_touchEndDeferringGestureRecognizerForImmediatelyResettableGestures);
1947 add(_touchEndDeferringGestureRecognizerForDelayedResettableGestures);
1948 add(_touchEndDeferringGestureRecognizerForSyntheticTapGestures);
1949 return [NSArray arrayWithObjects:recognizers count:count];
1950}

1976static NSValue *nsSizeForTapHighlightBorderRadius(WebCore::IntSize borderRadius, CGFloat borderRadiusScale)
1977{
1978 return [NSValue valueWithCGSize:CGSizeMake((borderRadius.width() * borderRadiusScale) + minimumTapHighlightRadius, (borderRadius.height() * borderRadiusScale) + minimumTapHighlightRadius)];
1979}
1980
1981- (void)_updateTapHighlight
1982{
1983 if (![_highlightView superview])
1984 return;
1985
1986 [_highlightView setColor:adoptNS([[UIColor alloc] initWithCGColor:cachedCGColor(_tapHighlightInformation.color)]).get()];
1987
1988 auto& highlightedQuads = _tapHighlightInformation.quads;
1989 bool allRectilinear = true;
1990 for (auto& quad : highlightedQuads) {
1991 if (!quad.isRectilinear()) {
1992 allRectilinear = false;
1993 break;
1994 }
1995 }
1996
1997 auto selfScale = self.layer.transform.m11;
1998 if (allRectilinear) {
1999 float deviceScaleFactor = _page->deviceScaleFactor();
2000 auto rects = createNSArray(highlightedQuads, [&] (auto& quad) {
2001 auto boundingBox = quad.boundingBox();
2002 boundingBox.scale(selfScale);
2003 boundingBox.inflate(minimumTapHighlightRadius);
2004 return [NSValue valueWithCGRect:encloseRectToDevicePixels(boundingBox, deviceScaleFactor)];
2005 });
2006 [_highlightView setFrames:rects.get() boundaryRect:_page->exposedContentRect()];
2007 } else {
2008 auto quads = adoptNS([[NSMutableArray alloc] initWithCapacity:highlightedQuads.size() * 4]);
2009 for (auto quad : highlightedQuads) {
2010 quad.scale(selfScale);
2011 auto extendedQuad = inflateQuad(quad, minimumTapHighlightRadius);
2012 [quads addObject:[NSValue valueWithCGPoint:extendedQuad.p1()]];
2013 [quads addObject:[NSValue valueWithCGPoint:extendedQuad.p2()]];
2014 [quads addObject:[NSValue valueWithCGPoint:extendedQuad.p3()]];
2015 [quads addObject:[NSValue valueWithCGPoint:extendedQuad.p4()]];
2016 }
2017 [_highlightView setQuads:quads.get() boundaryRect:_page->exposedContentRect()];
2018 }
2019
2020 [_highlightView setCornerRadii:@[
2021 nsSizeForTapHighlightBorderRadius(_tapHighlightInformation.topLeftRadius, selfScale),
2022 nsSizeForTapHighlightBorderRadius(_tapHighlightInformation.topRightRadius, selfScale),
2023 nsSizeForTapHighlightBorderRadius(_tapHighlightInformation.bottomLeftRadius, selfScale),
2024 nsSizeForTapHighlightBorderRadius(_tapHighlightInformation.bottomRightRadius, selfScale),
2025 ]];
2026}
2027
2028- (CGRect)tapHighlightViewRect
2029{
2030 return [_highlightView frame];
2031}

2039#endif

2042- (void)_showTapHighlight
2043{
2044 auto shouldPaintTapHighlight = [&](const WebCore::FloatRect& rect) {
2045#if PLATFORM(MACCATALYST)
2046 UNUSED_PARAM(rect);
2047 return NO;
2048#else
2049 if (_tapHighlightInformation.nodeHasBuiltInClickHandling)
2050 return true;
2051
2052 static const float highlightPaintThreshold = 0.3; // 30%
2053 float highlightArea = 0;
2054 for (auto highlightQuad : _tapHighlightInformation.quads) {
2055 auto boundingBox = highlightQuad.boundingBox();
2056 highlightArea += boundingBox.area();
2057 if (boundingBox.width() > (rect.width() * highlightPaintThreshold) || boundingBox.height() > (rect.height() * highlightPaintThreshold))
2058 return false;
2059 }
2060 return highlightArea < rect.area() * highlightPaintThreshold;
2061#endif
2062 };
2063
2064 if (!shouldPaintTapHighlight(_page->unobscuredContentRect()) && !_showDebugTapHighlightsForFastClicking)
2065 return;
2066
2067 if (!_highlightView) {
2068 _highlightView = adoptNS([[_UIHighlightView alloc] initWithFrame:CGRectZero]);
2069 [_highlightView setUserInteractionEnabled:NO];
2070 [_highlightView setOpaque:NO];
2071 [_highlightView setCornerRadius:minimumTapHighlightRadius];
2072 }
2073 [_highlightView layer].opacity = 1;
2074 [_interactionViewsContainerView addSubview:_highlightView.get()];
2075 [self _updateTapHighlight];
2076}
2077
2078- (void)_didGetTapHighlightForRequest:(uint64_t)requestID color:(const WebCore::Color&)color quads:(const Vector<WebCore::FloatQuad>&)highlightedQuads topLeftRadius:(const WebCore::IntSize&)topLeftRadius topRightRadius:(const WebCore::IntSize&)topRightRadius bottomLeftRadius:(const WebCore::IntSize&)bottomLeftRadius bottomRightRadius:(const WebCore::IntSize&)bottomRightRadius nodeHasBuiltInClickHandling:(BOOL)nodeHasBuiltInClickHandling
2079{
2080 if (!_isTapHighlightIDValid || _latestTapID != requestID)
2081 return;
2082
2083 if (self._hasFocusedElement && _positionInformation.elementContext && _positionInformation.elementContext->isSameElement(_focusedElementInformation.elementContext))
2084 return;
2085
2086 _isTapHighlightIDValid = NO;
2087
2088 _tapHighlightInformation.quads = highlightedQuads;
2089 _tapHighlightInformation.topLeftRadius = topLeftRadius;
2090 _tapHighlightInformation.topRightRadius = topRightRadius;
2091 _tapHighlightInformation.bottomLeftRadius = bottomLeftRadius;
2092 _tapHighlightInformation.bottomRightRadius = bottomRightRadius;
2093 _tapHighlightInformation.nodeHasBuiltInClickHandling = nodeHasBuiltInClickHandling;
2094 if (_showDebugTapHighlightsForFastClicking)
2095 _tapHighlightInformation.color = [self _tapHighlightColorForFastClick:![_doubleTapGestureRecognizer isEnabled]];
2096 else
2097 _tapHighlightInformation.color = color;
2098
2099 if (_potentialTapInProgress) {
2100 _hasTapHighlightForPotentialTap = YES;
2101 return;
2102 }
2103
2104 [self _showTapHighlight];
2105 if (_isExpectingFastSingleTapCommit) {
2106 [self _finishInteraction];
2107 if (!_potentialTapInProgress)
2108 _isExpectingFastSingleTapCommit = NO;
2109 }
2110}

2115}

2117- (void)_disableDoubleTapGesturesDuringTapIfNecessary:(uint64_t)requestID
2118{
2119 if (_latestTapID != requestID)
2120 return;
2121
2122 [self _setDoubleTapGesturesEnabled:NO];
2123}
2124
2125- (void)_handleSmartMagnificationInformationForPotentialTap:(uint64_t)requestID renderRect:(const WebCore::FloatRect&)renderRect fitEntireRect:(BOOL)fitEntireRect viewportMinimumScale:(double)viewportMinimumScale viewportMaximumScale:(double)viewportMaximumScale nodeIsRootLevel:(BOOL)nodeIsRootLevel
2126{
2127 const auto& preferences = _page->preferences();
2128
2129 ASSERT(preferences.fasterClicksEnabled());
2130 if (!_potentialTapInProgress)
2131 return;
2132
2133 // We check both the system preference and the page preference, because we only want this
2134 // to apply in "desktop" mode.
2135 if (preferences.preferFasterClickOverDoubleTap() && _page->preferFasterClickOverDoubleTap()) {
2136 RELEASE_LOG(ViewGestures, "Potential tap found an element and fast taps are preferred. Trigger click. (%p)", self);
2137 if (preferences.zoomOnDoubleTapWhenRoot() && nodeIsRootLevel) {
2138 RELEASE_LOG(ViewGestures, "The click handler was on a root-level element, so don't disable double-tap. (%p)", self);
2139 return;
2140 }
2141
2142 if (preferences.alwaysZoomOnDoubleTap()) {
2143 RELEASE_LOG(ViewGestures, "DTTZ is forced on, so don't disable double-tap. (%p)", self);
2144 return;
2145 }
2146
2147 RELEASE_LOG(ViewGestures, "Give preference to click by disabling double-tap. (%p)", self);
2148 [self _setDoubleTapGesturesEnabled:NO];
2149 return;
2150 }
2151
2152 auto currentScale = self._contentZoomScale;
2153 auto targetScale = _smartMagnificationController->zoomFactorForTargetRect(renderRect, fitEntireRect, viewportMinimumScale, viewportMaximumScale);
2154 if (std::min(targetScale, currentScale) / std::max(targetScale, currentScale) > fasterTapSignificantZoomThreshold) {
2155 RELEASE_LOG(ViewGestures, "Potential tap would not cause a significant zoom. Trigger click. (%p)", self);
2156 [self _setDoubleTapGesturesEnabled:NO];
2157 return;
2158 }
2159 RELEASE_LOG(ViewGestures, "Potential tap may cause significant zoom. Wait. (%p)", self);
2160}

2210- (BOOL)_shouldShowAutomaticKeyboardUIIgnoringInputMode
2211{
2212 if (_focusedElementInformation.isReadOnly)
2213 return NO;
2214
2215 switch (_focusedElementInformation.elementType) {
2216 case WebKit::InputType::None:
2217#if ENABLE(INPUT_TYPE_COLOR)
2218 case WebKit::InputType::Color:
2219#endif
2220 case WebKit::InputType::Drawing:
2221 case WebKit::InputType::Date:
2222 case WebKit::InputType::Month:
2223 case WebKit::InputType::DateTimeLocal:
2224 case WebKit::InputType::Time:
2225 return NO;
2226 case WebKit::InputType::Select: {
2227#if ENABLE(IOS_FORM_CONTROL_REFRESH)
2228 if (self._shouldUseContextMenusForFormControls)
2229 return NO;
2230#endif
2231 return !WebKit::currentUserInterfaceIdiomIsPadOrMac();
2232 }
2233 default:
2234 return YES;
2235 }
2236 return NO;
2237}

2263- (WebCore::FloatRect)rectToRevealWhenZoomingToFocusedElement
2264{

2266 if (_focusedElementInformation.interactionRect.contains(_focusedElementInformation.lastInteractionLocation))
2267 elementInteractionRect = { _focusedElementInformation.lastInteractionLocation, { 1, 1 } };

2273 return elementInteractionRect;

2276 boundingRect.intersect(_focusedElementInformation.interactionRect);

2280- (void)_zoomToRevealFocusedElement
2281{
2282 if (_suppressSelectionAssistantReasons || _activeTextInteractionCount)
2283 return;
2284
2285 // In case user scaling is force enabled, do not use that scaling when zooming in with an input field.
2286 // Zooming above the page's default scale factor should only happen when the user performs it.
2287 [self _zoomToFocusRect:_focusedElementInformation.interactionRect
2288 selectionRect:_didAccessoryTabInitiateFocus ? WebCore::FloatRect() : self.rectToRevealWhenZoomingToFocusedElement
2289 fontSize:_focusedElementInformation.nodeFontSize
2290 minimumScale:_focusedElementInformation.minimumScaleFactor
2291 maximumScale:_focusedElementInformation.maximumScaleFactorIgnoringAlwaysScalable
2292 allowScaling:_focusedElementInformation.allowsUserScalingIgnoringAlwaysScalable && !WebKit::currentUserInterfaceIdiomIsPadOrMac()
2293 forceScroll:[self requiresAccessoryView]];
2294}

2300
2301- (UIView *)inputViewForWebView
2302{
2303 if (!self._hasFocusedElement)
2304 return nil;
2305
2306 if (_inputPeripheral) {
2307 // FIXME: UIKit may invoke -[WKContentView inputView] at any time when WKContentView is the first responder;
2308 // as such, it doesn't make sense to change the enclosing scroll view's zoom scale and content offset to reveal
2309 // the focused element here. It seems this behavior was added to match logic in legacy WebKit (refer to
2310 // UIWebBrowserView). Instead, we should find the places where we currently assume that UIKit (or other clients)
2311 // invoke -inputView to zoom to the focused element, and either surface SPI for clients to zoom to the focused
2312 // element, or explicitly trigger the zoom from WebKit.
2313 // For instance, one use case that currently relies on this detail is adjusting the zoom scale and viewport upon
2314 // rotation, when a select element is focused. See <https://webkit.org/b/192878> for more information.
2315 [self _zoomToRevealFocusedElement];
2316
2317 [self _updateAccessory];
2318 }
2319
2320 if (UIView *customInputView = [_formInputSession customInputView])
2321 return customInputView;
2322
2323#if ENABLE(DATALIST_ELEMENT)
2324 if (_dataListTextSuggestionsInputView)
2325 return _dataListTextSuggestionsInputView.get();
2326#endif
2327
2328 return [_inputPeripheral assistantView];
2329}

2332{
2333 if (_page->waitingForPostLayoutEditorStateUpdateAfterFocusingElement())
2334 return _focusedElementInformation.interactionRect;
2335
2336 if (!_page->editorState().postLayoutData().selectionClipRect.isEmpty())
2337 return _page->editorState().postLayoutData().selectionClipRect;
2338
2339 return CGRectNull;
2340}

2342static BOOL isBuiltInScrollViewGestureRecognizer(UIGestureRecognizer *recognizer)
2343{
2344 return ([recognizer isKindOfClass:NSClassFromString(@"UIScrollViewPanGestureRecognizer")]
2345 || [recognizer isKindOfClass:NSClassFromString(@"UIScrollViewPinchGestureRecognizer")]
2346 || [recognizer isKindOfClass:NSClassFromString(@"UIScrollViewKnobLongPressGestureRecognizer")]
2347 );
2348}

2350- (BOOL)gestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)preventingGestureRecognizer canPreventGestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)preventedGestureRecognizer
2351{
2352 // A long-press gesture can not be recognized while panning, but a pan can be recognized
2353 // during a long-press gesture.
2354 BOOL shouldNotPreventScrollViewGestures = preventingGestureRecognizer == _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer || preventingGestureRecognizer == _longPressGestureRecognizer;
2355
2356 return !(shouldNotPreventScrollViewGestures && isBuiltInScrollViewGestureRecognizer(preventedGestureRecognizer));
2357}
2358
2359- (BOOL)gestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)preventedGestureRecognizer canBePreventedByGestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)preventingGestureRecognizer {
2360 // Don't allow the highlight to be prevented by a selection gesture. Press-and-hold on a link should highlight the link, not select it.
2361 bool isForcePressGesture = NO;
2362// FIXME: Likely we can remove this special case for watchOS and tvOS.
2363#if !PLATFORM(WATCHOS) && !PLATFORM(APPLETV)
2364 isForcePressGesture = (preventingGestureRecognizer == _textInteractionAssistant.get().forcePressGesture);
2365#endif
2366#if PLATFORM(MACCATALYST)
2367 if ((preventingGestureRecognizer == _textInteractionAssistant.get().loupeGesture) && (preventedGestureRecognizer == _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer || preventedGestureRecognizer == _longPressGestureRecognizer || preventedGestureRecognizer == _textInteractionAssistant.get().forcePressGesture))
2368 return YES;
2369#endif
2370
2371 if ((preventingGestureRecognizer == _textInteractionAssistant.get().loupeGesture || isForcePressGesture) && (preventedGestureRecognizer == _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer || preventedGestureRecognizer == _longPressGestureRecognizer))
2372 return NO;
2373
2374 return YES;
2375}

2377static inline bool isSamePair(UIGestureRecognizer *a, UIGestureRecognizer *b, UIGestureRecognizer *x, UIGestureRecognizer *y)
2378{
2379 return (a == x && b == y) || (b == x && a == y);
2380}
2381
2382- (BOOL)gestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer shouldRecognizeSimultaneouslyWithGestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer*)otherGestureRecognizer
2383{
2384 for (WKDeferringGestureRecognizer *gesture in self.deferringGestures) {
2385 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, _touchEventGestureRecognizer.get(), gesture))
2386 return YES;
2387 }
2388
2389 if ([gestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:WKDeferringGestureRecognizer.class] && [otherGestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:WKDeferringGestureRecognizer.class])
2390 return YES;
2391
2392#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
2393 if (gestureRecognizer == _imageAnalysisDeferringGestureRecognizer)
2394 return ![self shouldDeferGestureDueToImageAnalysis:otherGestureRecognizer];
2395
2396 if (otherGestureRecognizer == _imageAnalysisDeferringGestureRecognizer)
2397 return ![self shouldDeferGestureDueToImageAnalysis:gestureRecognizer];
2398#endif
2399
2400 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer.get(), _longPressGestureRecognizer.get()))
2401 return YES;
2402
2403#if HAVE(UIKIT_WITH_MOUSE_SUPPORT)
2404 if ([gestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:[WKMouseGestureRecognizer class]] || [otherGestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:[WKMouseGestureRecognizer class]])
2405 return YES;
2406#endif
2407
2408#if ENABLE(HOVER_GESTURE_RECOGNIZER)
2409 if ([gestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:[WKHoverGestureRecognizer class]] || [otherGestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:[WKHoverGestureRecognizer class]])
2410 return YES;
2411#endif
2412
2413#if PLATFORM(MACCATALYST)
2414 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, [_textInteractionAssistant loupeGesture], [_textInteractionAssistant forcePressGesture]))
2415 return YES;
2416
2417 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, _singleTapGestureRecognizer.get(), [_textInteractionAssistant loupeGesture]))
2418 return YES;
2419
2420 if (([gestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:[_UILookupGestureRecognizer class]] && [otherGestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:[UILongPressGestureRecognizer class]]) || ([otherGestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:[UILongPressGestureRecognizer class]] && [gestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:[_UILookupGestureRecognizer class]]))
2421 return YES;
2422#endif // PLATFORM(MACCATALYST)
2423
2424 if (gestureRecognizer == _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer.get() || otherGestureRecognizer == _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer.get()) {
2425 auto forcePressGesture = [_textInteractionAssistant forcePressGesture];
2426 if (gestureRecognizer == forcePressGesture || otherGestureRecognizer == forcePressGesture)
2427 return YES;
2428
2429 auto loupeGesture = [_textInteractionAssistant loupeGesture];
2430 if (gestureRecognizer == loupeGesture || otherGestureRecognizer == loupeGesture)
2431 return YES;
2432
2433 if (gestureRecognizer._wk_isTapAndAHalf || otherGestureRecognizer._wk_isTapAndAHalf)
2434 return YES;
2435 }
2436
2437 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, _singleTapGestureRecognizer.get(), [_textInteractionAssistant singleTapGesture]))
2438 return YES;
2439
2440 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, _singleTapGestureRecognizer.get(), _nonBlockingDoubleTapGestureRecognizer.get()))
2441 return YES;
2442
2443 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer.get(), _nonBlockingDoubleTapGestureRecognizer.get()))
2444 return YES;
2445
2446 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer.get(), _previewSecondaryGestureRecognizer.get()))
2447 return YES;
2448
2449 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer.get(), _previewGestureRecognizer.get()))
2450 return YES;
2451
2452 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, _nonBlockingDoubleTapGestureRecognizer.get(), _doubleTapGestureRecognizerForDoubleClick.get()))
2453 return YES;
2454
2455 if (isSamePair(gestureRecognizer, otherGestureRecognizer, _doubleTapGestureRecognizer.get(), _doubleTapGestureRecognizerForDoubleClick.get()))
2456 return YES;
2457
2458#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
2459 if (gestureRecognizer == _imageAnalysisGestureRecognizer || gestureRecognizer == _imageAnalysisTimeoutGestureRecognizer)
2460 return YES;
2461#endif
2462
2463 return NO;
2464}
2465
2466- (BOOL)gestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer shouldRequireFailureOfGestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)otherGestureRecognizer
2467{
2468 if (gestureRecognizer == _touchEventGestureRecognizer && [self _touchEventsMustRequireGestureRecognizerToFail:otherGestureRecognizer])
2469 return YES;
2470
2471 if ([otherGestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:WKDeferringGestureRecognizer.class])
2472 return [(WKDeferringGestureRecognizer *)otherGestureRecognizer shouldDeferGestureRecognizer:gestureRecognizer];
2473
2474#if USE(UICONTEXTMENU) && ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
2475 if (gestureRecognizer == _imageAnalysisTimeoutGestureRecognizer && otherGestureRecognizer == [_contextMenuInteraction gestureRecognizerForFailureRelationships])
2476 return YES;
2477#endif
2478
2479 return NO;
2480}
2481
2482- (BOOL)gestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer shouldBeRequiredToFailByGestureRecognizer:(UIGestureRecognizer *)otherGestureRecognizer
2483{
2484 if ([gestureRecognizer isKindOfClass:WKDeferringGestureRecognizer.class])
2485 return [(WKDeferringGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer shouldDeferGestureRecognizer:otherGestureRecognizer];
2486
2487#if USE(UICONTEXTMENU) && ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
2488 if (gestureRecognizer == [_contextMenuInteraction gestureRecognizerForFailureRelationships] && otherGestureRecognizer == _imageAnalysisTimeoutGestureRecognizer)
2489 return YES;
2490#endif
2491
2492 return NO;
2493}

2556- (void)doAfterPositionInformationUpdate:(void (^)(WebKit::InteractionInformationAtPosition))action forRequest:(WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest)request
2557{
2558 if ([self _currentPositionInformationIsValidForRequest:request]) {
2559 // If the most recent position information is already valid, invoke the given action block immediately.
2560 action(_positionInformation);
2561 return;
2562 }
2563
2564 _pendingPositionInformationHandlers.append(InteractionInformationRequestAndCallback(request, action));
2565
2566 if (![self _hasValidOutstandingPositionInformationRequest:request])
2567 [self requestAsynchronousPositionInformationUpdate:request];
2568}
2569
2570- (BOOL)ensurePositionInformationIsUpToDate:(WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest)request
2571{
2572 if ([self _currentPositionInformationIsValidForRequest:request])
2573 return YES;
2574
2575 if (!_page->hasRunningProcess())
2576 return NO;
2577
2578 auto* connection = _page->process().connection();
2579 if (!connection)
2580 return NO;
2581
2582 if (_isWaitingOnPositionInformation)
2583 return NO;
2584
2585 _isWaitingOnPositionInformation = YES;
2586 if (![self _hasValidOutstandingPositionInformationRequest:request])
2587 [self requestAsynchronousPositionInformationUpdate:request];
2588 bool receivedResponse = connection->waitForAndDispatchImmediately<Messages::WebPageProxy::DidReceivePositionInformation>(_page->webPageID(), 1_s, IPC::WaitForOption::InterruptWaitingIfSyncMessageArrives);
2589 _hasValidPositionInformation = receivedResponse && _positionInformation.canBeValid;
2590 return _hasValidPositionInformation;
2591}
2592
2593- (void)requestAsynchronousPositionInformationUpdate:(WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest)request
2594{
2595 if ([self _currentPositionInformationIsValidForRequest:request])
2596 return;
2597
2598 _lastOutstandingPositionInformationRequest = request;
2599
2600 _page->requestPositionInformation(request);
2601}

2608- (BOOL)_hasValidOutstandingPositionInformationRequest:(const WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest&)request

2613- (BOOL)_currentPositionInformationIsApproximatelyValidForRequest:(const WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest&)request radiusForApproximation:(int)radius
2614{

2618- (void)_invokeAndRemovePendingHandlersValidForCurrentPositionInformation
2619{
2620 ASSERT(_hasValidPositionInformation);
2621
2622 // FIXME: We need to clean up these handlers in the event that we are not able to collect data, or if the WebProcess crashes.
2623 ++_positionInformationCallbackDepth;
2624 auto updatedPositionInformation = _positionInformation;
2625
2626 for (size_t index = 0; index < _pendingPositionInformationHandlers.size(); ++index) {
2627 auto requestAndHandler = _pendingPositionInformationHandlers[index];
2628 if (!requestAndHandler)
2629 continue;
2630
2631 if (![self _currentPositionInformationIsValidForRequest:requestAndHandler->first])
2632 continue;
2633
2634 _pendingPositionInformationHandlers[index] = std::nullopt;
2635
2636 if (requestAndHandler->second)
2637 requestAndHandler->second(updatedPositionInformation);
2638 }
2639
2640 if (--_positionInformationCallbackDepth)
2641 return;
2642
2643 for (int index = _pendingPositionInformationHandlers.size() - 1; index >= 0; --index) {
2644 if (!_pendingPositionInformationHandlers[index])
2645 _pendingPositionInformationHandlers.remove(index);
2646 }
2647}

2651{
2652 return _page->dataDetectionResults();
2653}
2654#endif

2661 for (WKTextSelectionRect *selectionRect in [_textInteractionAssistant valueForKeyPath:@"selectionView.selection.selectionRects"])
2662 [textSelectionRects addObject:[NSValue valueWithCGRect:selectionRect.rect]];

2668- (BOOL)_pointIsInsideSelectionRect:(CGPoint)point outBoundingRect:(WebCore::FloatRect *)outBoundingRect
2669{
2670 BOOL pointIsInSelectionRect = NO;
2671 for (auto& rectInfo : _lastSelectionDrawingInfo.selectionGeometries) {
2672 auto rect = rectInfo.rect();
2673 if (rect.isEmpty())
2674 continue;
2675
2676 pointIsInSelectionRect |= rect.contains(WebCore::roundedIntPoint(point));
2677 if (outBoundingRect)
2678 outBoundingRect->unite(rect);
2679 }
2680 return pointIsInSelectionRect;
2681}
2682
2683- (BOOL)_shouldToggleSelectionCommandsAfterTapAt:(CGPoint)point
2684{
2685 if (_lastSelectionDrawingInfo.selectionGeometries.isEmpty())
2686 return NO;
2687
2688 WebCore::FloatRect selectionBoundingRect;
2689 BOOL pointIsInSelectionRect = [self _pointIsInsideSelectionRect:point outBoundingRect:&selectionBoundingRect];
2690 WebCore::FloatRect unobscuredContentRect = self.unobscuredContentRect;
2691 selectionBoundingRect.intersect(unobscuredContentRect);
2692
2693 float unobscuredArea = unobscuredContentRect.area();
2694 float ratioForConsideringSelectionRectToCoverVastMajorityOfContent = 0.75;
2695 if (!unobscuredArea || selectionBoundingRect.area() / unobscuredArea > ratioForConsideringSelectionRectToCoverVastMajorityOfContent)
2696 return NO;
2697
2698 return pointIsInSelectionRect;
2699}

2701- (BOOL)gestureRecognizerShouldBegin:(UIGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
2702{
2703 CGPoint point = [gestureRecognizer locationInView:self];
2704
2705 auto isInterruptingDecelerationForScrollViewOrAncestor = [&] (UIScrollView *scrollView) {
2706 UIScrollView *mainScroller = self.webView.scrollView;
2707 UIView *view = scrollView ?: mainScroller;
2708 while (view) {
2709 if ([view isKindOfClass:UIScrollView.class] && [(UIScrollView *)view _isInterruptingDeceleration])
2710 return YES;
2711
2712 if (mainScroller == view)
2713 break;
2714
2715 view = view.superview;
2716 }
2717 return NO;
2718 };
2719
2720 if (gestureRecognizer == _singleTapGestureRecognizer) {
2721 if ([self _shouldToggleSelectionCommandsAfterTapAt:point])
2722 return NO;
2723 return !isInterruptingDecelerationForScrollViewOrAncestor([_singleTapGestureRecognizer lastTouchedScrollView]);
2724 }
2725
2726 if (gestureRecognizer == _doubleTapGestureRecognizerForDoubleClick) {
2727 // Do not start the double-tap-for-double-click gesture recognizer unless we've got a dblclick event handler on the node at the tap location.
2728 WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest request(WebCore::roundedIntPoint(point));
2729 if (![self _currentPositionInformationIsApproximatelyValidForRequest:request radiusForApproximation:[_doubleTapGestureRecognizerForDoubleClick allowableMovement]]) {
2730 if (![self ensurePositionInformationIsUpToDate:request])
2731 return NO;
2732 }
2733 return _positionInformation.nodeAtPositionHasDoubleClickHandler.value_or(false);
2734 }
2735
2736 if (gestureRecognizer == _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer
2737 || gestureRecognizer == _doubleTapGestureRecognizer
2738 || gestureRecognizer == _nonBlockingDoubleTapGestureRecognizer
2739 || gestureRecognizer == _twoFingerDoubleTapGestureRecognizer) {
2740
2741 if (self._hasFocusedElement) {
2742 // Request information about the position with sync message.
2743 // If the focused element is the same, prevent the gesture.
2744 if (![self ensurePositionInformationIsUpToDate:WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest(WebCore::roundedIntPoint(point))])
2745 return NO;
2746 if (_positionInformation.elementContext && _positionInformation.elementContext->isSameElement(_focusedElementInformation.elementContext))
2747 return NO;
2748 }
2749 }
2750
2751 if (gestureRecognizer == _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer) {
2752 if (isInterruptingDecelerationForScrollViewOrAncestor([_highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer lastTouchedScrollView]))
2753 return NO;
2754
2755 if (self._hasFocusedElement) {
2756 // This is a different element than the focused one.
2757 // Prevent the gesture if there is no node.
2758 // Allow the gesture if it is a node that wants highlight or if there is an action for it.
2759 if (!_positionInformation.isElement)
2760 return NO;
2761 return [self _actionForLongPress] != nil;
2762 }
2763 // We still have no idea about what is at the location.
2764 // Send an async message to find out.
2765 _hasValidPositionInformation = NO;
2766 WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest request(WebCore::roundedIntPoint(point));
2767
2768 // If 3D Touch is enabled, asynchronously collect snapshots in the hopes that
2769 // they'll arrive before we have to synchronously request them in
2770 // _interactionShouldBeginFromPreviewItemController.
2771 if (self.traitCollection.forceTouchCapability == UIForceTouchCapabilityAvailable) {
2772 request.includeSnapshot = true;
2773 request.includeLinkIndicator = true;
2774 request.linkIndicatorShouldHaveLegacyMargins = !self._shouldUseContextMenus;
2775 }
2776
2777 [self requestAsynchronousPositionInformationUpdate:request];
2778 return YES;
2779
2780 }
2781
2782 if (gestureRecognizer == _longPressGestureRecognizer) {
2783 // Use the information retrieved with one of the previous calls
2784 // to gestureRecognizerShouldBegin.
2785 // Force a sync call if not ready yet.
2786 WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest request(WebCore::roundedIntPoint(point));
2787 if (![self ensurePositionInformationIsUpToDate:request])
2788 return NO;
2789
2790 if (self._hasFocusedElement) {
2791 // Prevent the gesture if it is the same node.
2792 if (_positionInformation.elementContext && _positionInformation.elementContext->isSameElement(_focusedElementInformation.elementContext))
2793 return NO;
2794 } else {
2795 // Prevent the gesture if there is no action for the node.
2796 return [self _actionForLongPress] != nil;
2797 }
2798 }
2799
2800 return YES;
2801}

2815- (void)_fadeTapHighlightViewIfNeeded
2816{
2817 if (![_highlightView superview] || _isTapHighlightFading)
2818 return;
2819
2820 _isTapHighlightFading = YES;
2821 CGFloat tapHighlightFadeDuration = _showDebugTapHighlightsForFastClicking ? 0.25 : 0.1;
2822 [UIView animateWithDuration:tapHighlightFadeDuration
2823 animations:^{
2824 [_highlightView layer].opacity = 0;
2825 }
2826 completion:^(BOOL finished) {
2827 if (finished)
2828 [_highlightView removeFromSuperview];
2829 _isTapHighlightFading = NO;
2830 }];
2831}

2889- (BOOL)textInteractionGesture:(UIWKGestureType)gesture shouldBeginAtPoint:(CGPoint)point
2890{
2891 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_BEGIN
2892 if (!self.webView.configuration._textInteractionGesturesEnabled)
2893 return NO;
2894 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_END
2895
2896 if (!_page->preferences().textInteractionEnabled())
2897 return NO;
2898
2899 if (_domPasteRequestHandler)
2900 return NO;
2901
2902 if (_suppressSelectionAssistantReasons)
2903 return NO;
2904
2905 if (!self.isFocusingElement) {
2906 if (gesture == UIWKGestureDoubleTap) {
2907 // Don't allow double tap text gestures in noneditable content.
2908 return NO;
2909 }
2910
2911 if (gesture == UIWKGestureOneFingerTap) {
2912 ASSERT(_suppressNonEditableSingleTapTextInteractionCount >= 0);
2913 if (_suppressNonEditableSingleTapTextInteractionCount > 0)
2914 return NO;
2915
2916 switch ([_textInteractionAssistant loupeGesture].state) {
2917 case UIGestureRecognizerStateBegan:
2918 case UIGestureRecognizerStateChanged:
2919 case UIGestureRecognizerStateEnded: {
2920 // Avoid handling one-finger taps while the web process is processing certain selection changes.
2921 // This works around a scenario where UIKeyboardImpl blocks the main thread while handling a one-
2922 // finger tap, which subsequently prevents the UI process from handling any incoming IPC messages.
2923 return NO;
2924 }
2925 default:
2926 return _page->editorState().selectionIsRange;
2927 }
2928 }
2929 }
2930
2931 WebKit::InteractionInformationRequest request(WebCore::roundedIntPoint(point));
2932 if (![self ensurePositionInformationIsUpToDate:request])
2933 return NO;
2934
2935#if ENABLE(DATALIST_ELEMENT)
2936 if (_positionInformation.preventTextInteraction)
2937 return NO;
2938#endif
2939
2940#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
2941 if (_elementPendingImageAnalysis && _positionInformation.imageElementContext == _elementPendingImageAnalysis)
2942 return YES;
2943#endif
2944
2945 // If we're currently focusing an editable element, only allow the selection to move within that focused element.
2946 if (self.isFocusingElement)
2947 return _positionInformation.elementContext && _positionInformation.elementContext->isSameElement(_focusedElementInformation.elementContext);
2948
2949 if (_positionInformation.prefersDraggingOverTextSelection)
2950 return NO;
2951
2952 // If we're selecting something, don't activate highlight.
2953 if (gesture == UIWKGestureLoupe && [self hasSelectablePositionAtPoint:point])
2954 [self _cancelLongPressGestureRecognizer];
2955
2956 // Otherwise, if we're using a text interaction assistant outside of editing purposes (e.g. the selection mode
2957 // is character granularity) then allow text selection.
2958 return YES;
2959}

2961- (NSArray *)webSelectionRectsForSelectionGeometries:(const Vector<WebCore::SelectionGeometry>&)selectionGeometries
2962{
2963 if (selectionGeometries.isEmpty())
2964 return nil;
2965
2966 return createNSArray(selectionGeometries, [] (auto& geometry) {
2967 auto webRect = [WebSelectionRect selectionRect];
2968 webRect.rect = geometry.rect();
2969 webRect.writingDirection = geometry.direction() == WebCore::TextDirection::LTR ? WKWritingDirectionLeftToRight : WKWritingDirectionRightToLeft;
2970 webRect.isLineBreak = geometry.isLineBreak();
2971 webRect.isFirstOnLine = geometry.isFirstOnLine();
2972 webRect.isLastOnLine = geometry.isLastOnLine();
2973 webRect.containsStart = geometry.containsStart();
2974 webRect.containsEnd = geometry.containsEnd();
2975 webRect.isInFixedPosition = geometry.isInFixedPosition();
2976 webRect.isHorizontal = geometry.isHorizontal();
2977 return webRect;
2978 }).autorelease();
2979}

2989- (void)_highlightLongPressRecognized:(UILongPressGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
2990{
2991 ASSERT(gestureRecognizer == _highlightLongPressGestureRecognizer);
2992 [self _resetIsDoubleTapPending];
2993
2994 _lastInteractionLocation = gestureRecognizer.startPoint;
2995
2996 switch ([gestureRecognizer state]) {
2997 case UIGestureRecognizerStateBegan:
2998 _longPressCanClick = YES;
2999 cancelPotentialTapIfNecessary(self);
3000 _page->tapHighlightAtPosition([gestureRecognizer startPoint], ++_latestTapID);
3001 _isTapHighlightIDValid = YES;
3002 break;
3003 case UIGestureRecognizerStateEnded:
3004 if (_longPressCanClick && _positionInformation.isElement) {
3005 [self _attemptSyntheticClickAtLocation:gestureRecognizer.startPoint modifierFlags:gestureRecognizerModifierFlags(gestureRecognizer)];
3006 [self _finishInteraction];
3007 } else
3008 [self _cancelInteraction];
3009 _longPressCanClick = NO;
3010 break;
3011 case UIGestureRecognizerStateCancelled:
3012 [self _cancelInteraction];
3013 _longPressCanClick = NO;
3014 break;
3015 default:
3016 break;
3017 }
3018}

3063- (void)_singleTapIdentified:(UITapGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
3064{
3065 ASSERT(gestureRecognizer == _singleTapGestureRecognizer);
3066 ASSERT(!_potentialTapInProgress);
3067 [self _resetIsDoubleTapPending];
3068
3069 bool shouldRequestMagnificationInformation = _page->preferences().fasterClicksEnabled();
3070 if (shouldRequestMagnificationInformation)
3071 RELEASE_LOG(ViewGestures, "Single tap identified. Request details on potential zoom. (%p)", self);
3072
3073 _page->potentialTapAtPosition(gestureRecognizer.location, shouldRequestMagnificationInformation, ++_latestTapID);
3074 _potentialTapInProgress = YES;
3075 _isTapHighlightIDValid = YES;
3076 _isExpectingFastSingleTapCommit = !_doubleTapGestureRecognizer.get().enabled;
3077}

3079static void cancelPotentialTapIfNecessary(WKContentView* contentView)
3080{
3081 if (contentView->_potentialTapInProgress) {
3082 [contentView _endPotentialTapAndEnableDoubleTapGesturesIfNecessary];
3083 [contentView _cancelInteraction];
3084 contentView->_page->cancelPotentialTap();
3085 }
3086}

3088- (void)_singleTapDidReset:(UITapGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
3089{
3090 ASSERT(gestureRecognizer == _singleTapGestureRecognizer);
3091 cancelPotentialTapIfNecessary(self);
3092 if (auto* singleTapTouchIdentifier = [_singleTapGestureRecognizer lastActiveTouchIdentifier]) {
3093 WebCore::PointerID pointerId = [singleTapTouchIdentifier unsignedIntValue];
3094 if (m_commitPotentialTapPointerId != pointerId)
3095 _page->touchWithIdentifierWasRemoved(pointerId);
3096 }
3097 auto actionsToPerform = std::exchange(_actionsToPerformAfterResettingSingleTapGestureRecognizer, { });
3098 for (const auto& action : actionsToPerform)
3099 action();
3100
3101 if (!_isTapHighlightIDValid)

3141- (void)_singleTapRecognized:(UITapGestureRecognizer *)gestureRecognizer
3142{
3143 ASSERT(gestureRecognizer == _singleTapGestureRecognizer);
3144
3145 if (![self isFirstResponder])
3146 [self becomeFirstResponder];
3147
3148 ASSERT(_potentialTapInProgress);
3149
3150 _lastInteractionLocation = gestureRecognizer.location;
3151
3152 [self _endPotentialTapAndEnableDoubleTapGesturesIfNecessary];
3153
3154 if (_hasTapHighlightForPotentialTap) {
3155 [self _showTapHighlight];
3156 _hasTapHighlightForPotentialTap = NO;
3157 }
3158
3159 [_inputPeripheral endEditing];
3160
3161 RELEASE_LOG(ViewGestures, "Single tap recognized - commit potential tap (%p)", self);
3162
3163 WebCore::PointerID pointerId = WebCore::mousePointerID;
3164 if (auto* singleTapTouchIdentifier = [_singleTapGestureRecognizer lastActiveTouchIdentifier]) {
3165 pointerId = [singleTapTouchIdentifier unsignedIntValue];
3166 m_commitPotentialTapPointerId = pointerId;
3167 }
3168 _page->commitPotentialTap(WebKit::webEventModifierFlags(gestureRecognizerModifierFlags(gestureRecognizer)), _layerTreeTransactionIdAtLastInteractionStart, pointerId);
3169
3170 if (!_isExpectingFastSingleTapCommit)
3171 [self _finishInteraction];
3172}

3398- (void)_lookupForWebView:(id)sender
3399{
3400 _page->getSelectionContext([view = retainPtr(self)](const String& selectedText, const String& textBefore, const String& textAfter) {
3401 if (!selectedText)
3402 return;
3403
3404 auto& editorState = view->_page->editorState();
3405 auto& postLayoutData = editorState.postLayoutData();
3406 CGRect presentationRect;
3407 if (editorState.selectionIsRange && !postLayoutData.selectionGeometries.isEmpty())
3408 presentationRect = view->_page->selectionBoundingRectInRootViewCoordinates();
3409 else
3410 presentationRect = postLayoutData.caretRectAtStart;
3411
3412 String selectionContext = textBefore + selectedText + textAfter;
3413 NSRange selectedRangeInContext = NSMakeRange(textBefore.length(), selectedText.length());
3414
3415 if (auto textSelectionAssistant = view->_textInteractionAssistant)
3416 [textSelectionAssistant lookup:selectionContext withRange:selectedRangeInContext fromRect:presentationRect];
3417 });
3418}

3428 if (selectionGeometries.isEmpty())

3435- (void)_translateForWebView:(id)sender
3436{
3437 _page->getSelectionOrContentsAsString([weakSelf = WeakObjCPtr<WKContentView>(self)] (const String& string) {
3438 if (!weakSelf)
3439 return;
3440
3441 if (string.isEmpty())
3442 return;
3443
3444 auto strongSelf = weakSelf.get();
3445 if (strongSelf->_page->editorState().isMissingPostLayoutData)
3446 return;

3449 return;

3453 });

3599- (NSDictionary *)textStylingAtPosition:(UITextPosition *)position inDirection:(UITextStorageDirection)direction
3600{
3601 if (!position || !_page->editorState().isContentRichlyEditable)
3602 return nil;
3603
3604 NSMutableDictionary* result = [NSMutableDictionary dictionary];
3605
3606 auto typingAttributes = _page->editorState().postLayoutData().typingAttributes;
3607 CTFontSymbolicTraits symbolicTraits = 0;
3608 if (typingAttributes & WebKit::AttributeBold)
3609 symbolicTraits |= kCTFontBoldTrait;
3610 if (typingAttributes & WebKit::AttributeItalics)
3611 symbolicTraits |= kCTFontTraitItalic;
3612
3613 // We chose a random font family and size.
3614 // What matters are the traits but the caller expects a font object
3615 // in the dictionary for NSFontAttributeName.
3616 RetainPtr<CTFontDescriptorRef> fontDescriptor = adoptCF(CTFontDescriptorCreateWithNameAndSize(CFSTR("Helvetica"), 10));
3617 if (symbolicTraits)
3618 fontDescriptor = adoptCF(CTFontDescriptorCreateCopyWithSymbolicTraits(fontDescriptor.get(), symbolicTraits, symbolicTraits));
3619
3620 RetainPtr<CTFontRef> font = adoptCF(CTFontCreateWithFontDescriptor(fontDescriptor.get(), 10, nullptr));
3621 if (font)
3622 [result setObject:(id)font.get() forKey:NSFontAttributeName];
3623
3624 if (typingAttributes & WebKit::AttributeUnderline)
3625 [result setObject:@(NSUnderlineStyleSingle) forKey:NSUnderlineStyleAttributeName];
3626
3627 return result;
3628}
