3695- (BOOL)canPerformAction:(SEL)action withSender:(id)sender
3696{
3697 if (_domPasteRequestHandler)
3698 return action == @selector(paste:);
3699
3700 // These are UIKit IPI selectors. We don't want to forward them to the web view.
3701 auto editorState = _page->editorState();
3702 if (action == @selector(_moveDown:withHistory:) || action == @selector(_moveLeft:withHistory:) || action == @selector(_moveRight:withHistory:)
3703 || action == @selector(_moveToEndOfDocument:withHistory:) || action == @selector(_moveToEndOfLine:withHistory:) || action == @selector(_moveToEndOfParagraph:withHistory:)
3704 || action == @selector(_moveToEndOfWord:withHistory:) || action == @selector(_moveToStartOfDocument:withHistory:) || action == @selector(_moveToStartOfLine:withHistory:)
3705 || action == @selector(_moveToStartOfParagraph:withHistory:) || action == @selector(_moveToStartOfWord:withHistory:) || action == @selector(_moveUp:withHistory:))
3706 return !editorState.selectionIsNone;
3707
3708 if (action == @selector(_deleteByWord) || action == @selector(_deleteForwardByWord) || action == @selector(_deleteForwardAndNotify:) || action == @selector(_deleteToEndOfParagraph) || action == @selector(_deleteToStartOfLine)
3709 || action == @selector(_transpose))
3710 return editorState.isContentEditable;
3711
3712 return [_webView canPerformAction:action withSender:sender];
3713}
3714
3715- (BOOL)canPerformActionForWebView:(SEL)action withSender:(id)sender
3716{
3717 if (_domPasteRequestHandler)
3718 return action == @selector(paste:);
3719
3720 if (action == @selector(_nextAccessoryTab:))
3721 return self._hasFocusedElement && _focusedElementInformation.hasNextNode;
3722 if (action == @selector(_previousAccessoryTab:))
3723 return self._hasFocusedElement && _focusedElementInformation.hasPreviousNode;
3724
3725 auto editorState = _page->editorState();
3726 if (action == @selector(_showTextStyleOptions:))
3727 return editorState.isContentRichlyEditable && editorState.selectionIsRange && !_showingTextStyleOptions;
3728 if (_showingTextStyleOptions)
3729 return (action == @selector(toggleBoldface:) || action == @selector(toggleItalics:) || action == @selector(toggleUnderline:));
3730 // FIXME: Some of the following checks should be removed once internal clients move to the underscore-prefixed versions.
3731 if (action == @selector(toggleBoldface:) || action == @selector(toggleItalics:) || action == @selector(toggleUnderline:) || action == @selector(_toggleStrikeThrough:)
3732 || action == @selector(_alignLeft:) || action == @selector(_alignRight:) || action == @selector(_alignCenter:) || action == @selector(_alignJustified:)
3733 || action == @selector(_setTextColor:sender:) || action == @selector(_setFont:sender:) || action == @selector(_setFontSize:sender:)
3734 || action == @selector(_insertOrderedList:) || action == @selector(_insertUnorderedList:) || action == @selector(_insertNestedOrderedList:) || action == @selector(_insertNestedUnorderedList:)
3735 || action == @selector(_increaseListLevel:) || action == @selector(_decreaseListLevel:) || action == @selector(_changeListType:) || action == @selector(_indent:) || action == @selector(_outdent:)
3736 || action == @selector(increaseSize:) || action == @selector(decreaseSize:) || action == @selector(makeTextWritingDirectionNatural:)) {
3737 // FIXME: This should be more nuanced in the future, rather than returning YES for all richly editable areas. For instance, outdent: should be disabled when the selection is already
3738 // at the outermost indentation level.
3739 return editorState.isContentRichlyEditable;
3740 }
3741 if (action == @selector(cut:))
3742 return !editorState.isInPasswordField && editorState.isContentEditable && editorState.selectionIsRange;
3743
3744 if (action == @selector(paste:) || action == @selector(_pasteAsQuotation:) || action == @selector(_pasteAndMatchStyle:) || action == @selector(pasteAndMatchStyle:)) {
3745 if (editorState.selectionIsNone || !editorState.isContentEditable)
3746 return NO;
3747 UIPasteboard *pasteboard = [UIPasteboard generalPasteboard];
3748 NSArray *types = [self supportedPasteboardTypesForCurrentSelection];
3749 NSIndexSet *indices = [NSIndexSet indexSetWithIndexesInRange:NSMakeRange(0, [pasteboard numberOfItems])];
3750 if ([pasteboard containsPasteboardTypes:types inItemSet:indices])
3751 return YES;
3752
3753#if PLATFORM(IOS)
3754 if (editorState.isContentRichlyEditable && self.webView.configuration._attachmentElementEnabled) {
3755 for (NSItemProvider *itemProvider in pasteboard.itemProviders) {
3756 auto preferredPresentationStyle = itemProvider.preferredPresentationStyle;
3757 if (preferredPresentationStyle == UIPreferredPresentationStyleInline)
3758 continue;
3759
3760 if (preferredPresentationStyle == UIPreferredPresentationStyleUnspecified && !itemProvider.suggestedName.length)
3761 continue;
3762
3763 if (itemProvider.web_fileUploadContentTypes.count)
3764 return YES;
3765 }
3766 }
3767#endif // PLATFORM(IOS)
3768
3769 auto focusedDocumentOrigin = editorState.originIdentifierForPasteboard;
3770 if (focusedDocumentOrigin.isEmpty())
3771 return NO;
3772
3773 NSArray *allCustomPasteboardData = [pasteboard dataForPasteboardType:@(WebCore::PasteboardCustomData::cocoaType()) inItemSet:indices];
3774 for (NSData *data in allCustomPasteboardData) {
3775 auto buffer = WebCore::SharedBuffer::create(data);
3776 if (WebCore::PasteboardCustomData::fromSharedBuffer(buffer.get()).origin() == focusedDocumentOrigin)
3777 return YES;
3778 }
3779 return NO;
3780 }
3781
3782 if (action == @selector(copy:)) {
3783 if (editorState.isInPasswordField)
3784 return NO;
3785 return editorState.selectionIsRange;
3786 }
3787
3788 if (action == @selector(_define:)) {
3789 if (editorState.isInPasswordField || !editorState.selectionIsRange)
3790 return NO;
3791
3792 NSUInteger textLength = editorState.postLayoutData().selectedTextLength;
3793 // FIXME: We should be calling UIReferenceLibraryViewController to check if the length is
3794 // acceptable, but the interface takes a string.
3795 // <rdar://problem/15254406>
3796 if (!textLength || textLength > 200)
3797 return NO;
3798
3799#if !PLATFORM(MACCATALYST)
3800 if ([[PAL::getMCProfileConnectionClass() sharedConnection] effectiveBoolValueForSetting:PAL::get_ManagedConfiguration_MCFeatureDefinitionLookupAllowed()] == MCRestrictedBoolExplicitNo)
3801 return NO;
3802#endif
3803
3804 return YES;
3805 }
3806
3807 if (action == @selector(_lookup:)) {
3808 if (editorState.isInPasswordField)
3809 return NO;
3810
3811#if !PLATFORM(MACCATALYST)
3812 if ([[PAL::getMCProfileConnectionClass() sharedConnection] effectiveBoolValueForSetting:PAL::get_ManagedConfiguration_MCFeatureDefinitionLookupAllowed()] == MCRestrictedBoolExplicitNo)
3813 return NO;
3814#endif
3815
3816 return editorState.selectionIsRange;
3817 }
3818
3819 if (action == @selector(_share:)) {
3820 if (editorState.isInPasswordField || !editorState.selectionIsRange)
3821 return NO;
3822
3823 return editorState.postLayoutData().selectedTextLength > 0;
3824 }
3825
3826 if (action == @selector(_addShortcut:)) {
3827 if (editorState.isInPasswordField || !editorState.selectionIsRange)
3828 return NO;
3829
3830 NSString *selectedText = [self selectedText];
3831 if (![selectedText length])
3832 return NO;
3833
3834 if (!UIKeyboardEnabledInputModesAllowOneToManyShortcuts())
3835 return NO;
3836 if (![selectedText _containsCJScripts])
3837 return NO;
3838 return YES;
3839 }
3840
3841 if (action == @selector(_promptForReplace:)) {
3842 if (!editorState.selectionIsRange || !editorState.postLayoutData().isReplaceAllowed || ![[UIKeyboardImpl activeInstance] autocorrectSpellingEnabled])
3843 return NO;
3844 if ([[self selectedText] _containsCJScriptsOnly])
3845 return NO;
3846 return YES;
3847 }
3848
3849 if (action == @selector(_transliterateChinese:)) {
3850 if (!editorState.selectionIsRange || !editorState.postLayoutData().isReplaceAllowed || ![[UIKeyboardImpl activeInstance] autocorrectSpellingEnabled])
3851 return NO;
3852 return UIKeyboardEnabledInputModesAllowChineseTransliterationForText([self selectedText]);
3853 }
3854
3855 if (action == @selector(_translate:))
3856 return !editorState.isInPasswordField && editorState.selectionIsRange;
3857
3858 if (action == @selector(select:)) {
3859 // Disable select in password fields so that you can't see word boundaries.
3860 return !editorState.isInPasswordField && !editorState.selectionIsRange && self.hasContent;
3861 }
3862
3863 if (action == @selector(selectAll:)) {
3864 if ([sender isKindOfClass:UIMenuController.class]) {
3865 // By platform convention we don't show Select All in the callout menu for a range selection.
3866 return !editorState.selectionIsRange && self.hasContent;
3867 }
3868 return YES;
3869 }
3870
3871 if (action == @selector(replace:))
3872 return editorState.isContentEditable && !editorState.isInPasswordField;
3873
3874 if (action == @selector(makeTextWritingDirectionLeftToRight:) || action == @selector(makeTextWritingDirectionRightToLeft:)) {
3875 if (!editorState.isContentEditable)
3876 return NO;
3877
3878 auto baseWritingDirection = editorState.postLayoutData().baseWritingDirection;
3879 if (baseWritingDirection == WebCore::WritingDirection::LeftToRight && !UIKeyboardIsRightToLeftInputModeActive()) {
3880 // A keyboard is considered "active" if it is available for the user to switch to. As such, this check prevents
3881 // text direction actions from showing up in the case where a user has only added left-to-right keyboards, and
3882 // is also not editing right-to-left content.
3883 return NO;
3884 }
3885
3886 if (action == @selector(makeTextWritingDirectionLeftToRight:))
3887 return baseWritingDirection != WebCore::WritingDirection::LeftToRight;
3888
3889 return baseWritingDirection != WebCore::WritingDirection::RightToLeft;
3890 }
3891
3892#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
3893 if (action == @selector(captureTextFromCamera:) && (!editorState.isContentEditable || editorState.selectionIsRange))
3894 return NO;
3895#endif
3896
3897 return [super canPerformAction:action withSender:sender];
3898}
3899
3900- (id)targetForAction:(SEL)action withSender:(id)sender
3901{
3902#if ENABLE(APP_HIGHLIGHTS)
3903 if (action == @selector(createHighlightForCurrentQuickNoteWithRange:))
3904 return self.shouldAllowAppHighlightCreation && _page->appHighlightsVisibility() ? self : nil;
3905 if (action == @selector(createHighlightForNewQuickNoteWithRange:))
3906 return self.shouldAllowAppHighlightCreation && !_page->appHighlightsVisibility() ? self : nil;
3907#endif
3908 return [_webView targetForAction:action withSender:sender];
3909}

4092- (BOOL)_handleDOMPasteRequestWithResult:(WebCore::DOMPasteAccessResponse)response
4093{

4095 _page->grantAccessToCurrentPasteboardData(UIPasteboardNameGeneral);
4096
4097 if (auto pasteHandler = WTFMove(_domPasteRequestHandler)) {
4098 [UIMenuController.sharedMenuController hideMenuFromView:self];
4099 pasteHandler(response);
4100 return YES;
4101 }
4102 return NO;
4103}

4119static inline WebKit::GestureType toGestureType(UIWKGestureType gestureType)
4120{
4121 switch (gestureType) {
4122 case UIWKGestureLoupe:
4123 return WebKit::GestureType::Loupe;
4124 case UIWKGestureOneFingerTap:
4125 return WebKit::GestureType::OneFingerTap;
4126 case UIWKGestureTapAndAHalf:
4127 return WebKit::GestureType::TapAndAHalf;
4128 case UIWKGestureDoubleTap:
4129 return WebKit::GestureType::DoubleTap;
4130 case UIWKGestureTapAndHalf:
4131 return WebKit::GestureType::TapAndHalf;
4132 case UIWKGestureDoubleTapInUneditable:
4133 return WebKit::GestureType::DoubleTapInUneditable;
4134 case UIWKGestureOneFingerTapInUneditable:
4135 return WebKit::GestureType::OneFingerTapInUneditable;
4136 case UIWKGestureOneFingerTapSelectsAll:
4137 return WebKit::GestureType::OneFingerTapSelectsAll;
4138 case UIWKGestureOneFingerDoubleTap:
4139 return WebKit::GestureType::OneFingerDoubleTap;
4140 case UIWKGestureOneFingerTripleTap:
4141 return WebKit::GestureType::OneFingerTripleTap;
4142 case UIWKGestureTwoFingerSingleTap:
4143 return WebKit::GestureType::TwoFingerSingleTap;
4144 case UIWKGestureTwoFingerRangedSelectGesture:
4145 return WebKit::GestureType::TwoFingerRangedSelectGesture;
4146 case UIWKGestureTapOnLinkWithGesture:
4147 return WebKit::GestureType::TapOnLinkWithGesture;
4148 case UIWKGesturePhraseBoundary:
4149 return WebKit::GestureType::PhraseBoundary;
4150 case UIWKGestureMakeWebSelection:
4151 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4152 return WebKit::GestureType::Loupe;
4153 }
4154 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4155 return WebKit::GestureType::Loupe;
4156}

4266static inline UIWKSelectionFlags toUIWKSelectionFlags(OptionSet<WebKit::SelectionFlags> flags)
4267{
4268 NSInteger uiFlags = UIWKNone;
4269 if (flags.contains(WebKit::WordIsNearTap))
4270 uiFlags |= UIWKWordIsNearTap;
4271 if (flags.contains(WebKit::PhraseBoundaryChanged))
4272 uiFlags |= UIWKPhraseBoundaryChanged;
4273
4274 return static_cast<UIWKSelectionFlags>(uiFlags);
4275}
4276
4277static inline OptionSet<WebKit::SelectionFlags> toSelectionFlags(UIWKSelectionFlags uiFlags)
4278{
4279 OptionSet<WebKit::SelectionFlags> flags;
4280 if (uiFlags & UIWKWordIsNearTap)
4281 flags.add(WebKit::WordIsNearTap);
4282 if (uiFlags & UIWKPhraseBoundaryChanged)
4283 flags.add(WebKit::PhraseBoundaryChanged);
4284 return flags;
4285}

4298 case UITextGranularityLine:

4305static inline WebCore::SelectionDirection toWKSelectionDirection(UITextDirection direction)
4306{
4307 switch (direction) {
4308 case UITextLayoutDirectionDown:
4309 case UITextLayoutDirectionRight:
4310 return WebCore::SelectionDirection::Right;
4311 case UITextLayoutDirectionUp:
4312 case UITextLayoutDirectionLeft:
4313 return WebCore::SelectionDirection::Left;
4314 default:
4315 // UITextDirection is not an enum, but we only want to accept values from UITextLayoutDirection.
4316 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4317 return WebCore::SelectionDirection::Right;
4318 }
4319}

4388// The completion handler can pass nil if input does not match the actual text preceding the insertion point.
4389- (void)requestAutocorrectionRectsForString:(NSString *)input withCompletionHandler:(void (^)(UIWKAutocorrectionRects *rectsForInput))completionHandler
4390{
4391 if (!completionHandler) {
4392 [NSException raise:NSInvalidArgumentException format:@"Expected a nonnull completion handler in %s.", __PRETTY_FUNCTION__];
4393 return;
4394 }
4395
4396 if (!input || ![input length]) {
4397 completionHandler(nil);
4398 return;
4399 }
4400
4401 _page->requestAutocorrectionData(input, [view = retainPtr(self), completion = makeBlockPtr(completionHandler)](auto data) {
4402 CGRect firstRect;
4403 CGRect lastRect;
4404 auto& rects = data.textRects;
4405 if (rects.isEmpty()) {
4406 firstRect = CGRectZero;
4407 lastRect = CGRectZero;
4408 } else {
4409 firstRect = rects.first();
4410 lastRect = rects.last();
4411 }
4412
4413 view->_autocorrectionData.font = data.font;
4414 view->_autocorrectionData.textFirstRect = firstRect;
4415 view->_autocorrectionData.textLastRect = lastRect;
4416
4417 completion(!rects.isEmpty() ? [WKAutocorrectionRects autocorrectionRectsWithFirstCGRect:firstRect lastCGRect:lastRect] : nil);
4418 });
4419}

4421- (void)requestRectsToEvadeForSelectionCommandsWithCompletionHandler:(void(^)(NSArray<NSValue *> *rects))completionHandler

4425 return;

4429 completionHandler(@[ ]);
4430 return;
4431 }

4433 if (_focusedElementInformation.elementType != WebKit::InputType::ContentEditable && _focusedElementInformation.elementType != WebKit::InputType::TextArea) {
4434 completionHandler(@[ ]);
4435 return;
4436 }

4438 // Give the page some time to present custom editing UI before attempting to detect and evade it.
4439 auto delayBeforeShowingCalloutBar = 0.25_s;
4440 WorkQueue::main().dispatchAfter(delayBeforeShowingCalloutBar, [completion = makeBlockPtr(completionHandler), weakSelf = WeakObjCPtr<WKContentView>(self)] () mutable {
4441 if (!weakSelf) {
4442 completion(@[ ]);
4443 return;
4444 }

4447 if (!strongSelf->_page) {
4448 completion(@[ ]);
4449 return;
4450 }

4454 });
4455 });

4550- (CGRect)textFirstRect
4551{

4553 if (editorState.hasComposition) {
4554 auto& markedTextRects = editorState.postLayoutData().markedTextRects;
4555 return markedTextRects.isEmpty() ? CGRectZero : markedTextRects.first().rect();
4556 }
4557 return _autocorrectionData.textFirstRect;
4558}

4560- (CGRect)textLastRect
4561{
4562 auto& editorState = _page->editorState();
4563 if (editorState.hasComposition) {
4564 auto& markedTextRects = editorState.postLayoutData().markedTextRects;
4565 return markedTextRects.isEmpty() ? CGRectZero : markedTextRects.last().rect();
4566 }
4567 return _autocorrectionData.textLastRect;

4582// The completion handler should pass the rect of the correction text after replacing the input text, or nil if the replacement could not be performed.
4583- (void)applyAutocorrection:(NSString *)correction toString:(NSString *)input withCompletionHandler:(void (^)(UIWKAutocorrectionRects *rectsForCorrection))completionHandler
4584{
4585#if USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
4586 if ([self _disableAutomaticKeyboardUI]) {
4587 if (completionHandler)
4588 completionHandler(nil);
4589 return;
4590 }
4591#endif
4592
4593 // FIXME: Remove the synchronous call when <rdar://problem/16207002> is fixed.
4594 const bool useSyncRequest = true;
4595
4596 if (useSyncRequest) {
4597 if (completionHandler)
4598 completionHandler(_page->applyAutocorrection(correction, input) ? [WKAutocorrectionRects autocorrectionRectsWithFirstCGRect:_autocorrectionData.textFirstRect lastCGRect:_autocorrectionData.textLastRect] : nil);
4599 return;
4600 }
4601
4602 _page->applyAutocorrection(correction, input, [view = retainPtr(self), completion = makeBlockPtr(completionHandler)](auto& string) {
4603 if (completion)
4604 completion(!string.isNull() ? [WKAutocorrectionRects autocorrectionRectsWithFirstCGRect:view->_autocorrectionData.textFirstRect lastCGRect:view->_autocorrectionData.textLastRect] : nil);
4605 });
4606}

4608- (void)_invokePendingAutocorrectionContextHandler:(WKAutocorrectionContext *)context
4609{
4610 if (auto handler = WTFMove(_pendingAutocorrectionContextHandler))
4611 handler(context);
4612}
4613
4614- (void)_cancelPendingAutocorrectionContextHandler
4615{
4616 [self _invokePendingAutocorrectionContextHandler:WKAutocorrectionContext.emptyAutocorrectionContext];
4617}
4618
4619- (void)requestAutocorrectionContextWithCompletionHandler:(void (^)(UIWKAutocorrectionContext *autocorrectionContext))completionHandler
4620{
4621 if (!completionHandler) {
4622 [NSException raise:NSInvalidArgumentException format:@"Expected a nonnull completion handler in %s.", __PRETTY_FUNCTION__];
4623 return;
4624 }
4625
4626#if USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
4627 if ([self _disableAutomaticKeyboardUI]) {
4628 completionHandler(WKAutocorrectionContext.emptyAutocorrectionContext);
4629 return;
4630 }
4631#endif
4632
4633 if (!_page->hasRunningProcess()) {
4634 completionHandler(WKAutocorrectionContext.emptyAutocorrectionContext);
4635 return;
4636 }
4637
4638 bool respondWithLastKnownAutocorrectionContext = ([&] {
4639 if (_page->isRunningModalJavaScriptDialog())
4640 return true;
4641
4642 if (_domPasteRequestHandler)
4643 return true;
4644
4645 if (_isUnsuppressingSoftwareKeyboardUsingLastAutocorrectionContext)
4646 return true;
4647
4648 return false;
4649 })();
4650
4651 if (respondWithLastKnownAutocorrectionContext) {
4652 completionHandler([WKAutocorrectionContext autocorrectionContextWithWebContext:_lastAutocorrectionContext]);
4653 return;
4654 }
4655
4656 // FIXME: Remove the synchronous call when <rdar://problem/16207002> is fixed.
4657 const bool useSyncRequest = true;
4658
4659 if (useSyncRequest && _pendingAutocorrectionContextHandler) {
4660 completionHandler(WKAutocorrectionContext.emptyAutocorrectionContext);
4661 return;
4662 }
4663
4664 _pendingAutocorrectionContextHandler = completionHandler;
4665 _page->requestAutocorrectionContext();
4666
4667 if (useSyncRequest) {
4668 _page->process().connection()->waitForAndDispatchImmediately<Messages::WebPageProxy::HandleAutocorrectionContext>(_page->webPageID(), 1_s, IPC::WaitForOption::DispatchIncomingSyncMessagesWhileWaiting);
4669 [self _cancelPendingAutocorrectionContextHandler];
4670 }
4671}
4672
4673- (void)_handleAutocorrectionContext:(const WebKit::WebAutocorrectionContext&)context
4674{
4675 _lastAutocorrectionContext = context;
4676 [self unsuppressSoftwareKeyboardUsingLastAutocorrectionContextIfNeeded];
4677 [self _invokePendingAutocorrectionContextHandler:[WKAutocorrectionContext autocorrectionContextWithWebContext:context]];
4678}

4680- (void)updateSoftwareKeyboardSuppressionStateFromWebView
4681{
4682 BOOL webViewIsSuppressingSoftwareKeyboard = [_webView _suppressSoftwareKeyboard];
4683 if (webViewIsSuppressingSoftwareKeyboard) {
4684 _unsuppressSoftwareKeyboardAfterNextAutocorrectionContextUpdate = NO;
4685 self._suppressSoftwareKeyboard = webViewIsSuppressingSoftwareKeyboard;
4686 return;
4687 }
4688
4689 if (self._suppressSoftwareKeyboard == webViewIsSuppressingSoftwareKeyboard)
4690 return;
4691
4692 if (!std::exchange(_unsuppressSoftwareKeyboardAfterNextAutocorrectionContextUpdate, YES))
4693 _page->requestAutocorrectionContext();
4694}
4695
4696- (void)unsuppressSoftwareKeyboardUsingLastAutocorrectionContextIfNeeded
4697{
4698 if (!std::exchange(_unsuppressSoftwareKeyboardAfterNextAutocorrectionContextUpdate, NO))
4699 return;
4700
4701 SetForScope<BOOL> unsuppressSoftwareKeyboardScope { _isUnsuppressingSoftwareKeyboardUsingLastAutocorrectionContext, YES };
4702 self._suppressSoftwareKeyboard = NO;
4703}

4713- (void)_didStartProvisionalLoadForMainFrame

4716 [_doubleTapGestureRecognizerForDoubleClick _wk_cancel];
4717 // We also need to disable the double-tap gesture recognizers that are enabled for double-tap-to-zoom and which
4718 // are enabled when a single tap is first recognized. This avoids tests running in sequence and simulating taps
4719 // in the same location to trigger double-tap recognition.
4720 [self _setDoubleTapGesturesEnabled:NO];
4721 [_twoFingerDoubleTapGestureRecognizer _wk_cancel];

4842- (void)accessoryTab:(BOOL)isNext
4843{
4844 // The input peripheral may need to update the focused DOM node before we switch focus. The UI process does
4845 // not maintain a handle to the actual focused DOM node only the web process has such a handle. So, we need
4846 // to end the editing session now before we tell the web process to switch focus. Once the web process tells
4847 // us the newly focused element we are no longer are in a position to effect the previously focused element.
4848 // See <https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=134409>.
4849 [self _endEditing];
4850 _inputPeripheral = nil; // Nullify so that we don't tell the input peripheral to end editing again in -_elementDidBlur.
4851
4852 _isChangingFocusUsingAccessoryTab = YES;
4853 [self beginSelectionChange];
4854 _page->focusNextFocusedElement(isNext, [protectedSelf = retainPtr(self)] {
4855 [protectedSelf endSelectionChange];
4856 [protectedSelf reloadInputViews];
4857 protectedSelf->_isChangingFocusUsingAccessoryTab = NO;
4858 });
4859}

4864 if ([inputDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:accessoryViewCustomButtonTappedInFormInputSession:)])
4865 [inputDelegate _webView:self.webView accessoryViewCustomButtonTappedInFormInputSession:_formInputSession.get()];
4866}

4873 [_formAccessoryView setDelegate:self];
4874 return _formAccessoryView.get();
4875}

4877- (void)accessoryOpen

4884}
4885
4886- (void)_updateAccessory
4887{
4888 auto* accessoryView = self.formAccessoryView; // Creates one, if needed.
4889
4890 if ([accessoryView respondsToSelector:@selector(setNextPreviousItemsVisible:)])
4891 [accessoryView setNextPreviousItemsVisible:!self.webView._editable];
4892
4893 [accessoryView setNextEnabled:_focusedElementInformation.hasNextNode];
4894 [accessoryView setPreviousEnabled:_focusedElementInformation.hasPreviousNode];
4895
4896 if (WebKit::currentUserInterfaceIdiomIsPadOrMac()) {
4897 [accessoryView setClearVisible:NO];
4898 return;
4899 }
4900
4901 switch (_focusedElementInformation.elementType) {
4902 case WebKit::InputType::Date:
4903 case WebKit::InputType::DateTimeLocal:
4904 case WebKit::InputType::Month:
4905 case WebKit::InputType::Time:
4906 [accessoryView setClearVisible:YES];
4907 return;
4908 default:
4909 [accessoryView setClearVisible:NO];
4910 return;
4911 }
4912}

4984static NSArray<WKTextSelectionRect *> *textSelectionRects(const Vector<WebCore::SelectionGeometry>& rects, CGFloat scaleFactor)
4985{
4986 return createNSArray(rects, [scaleFactor] (auto& rect) {

4990
4991- (WebCore::FloatRect)_scaledCaretRectForSelectionStart:(WebCore::FloatRect)caretRect
4992{
4993 // The logical height of the caret is scaled inversely by the view's zoom scale
4994 // to achieve the visual effect that the caret is narrow when zoomed in and wide
4995 // when zoomed out.
4996 double inverseScale = [self inverseScale];
4997 if (bool isHorizontalCaret = caretRect.width() < caretRect.height())
4998 caretRect.setWidth(caretRect.width() * inverseScale);
4999 else
5000 caretRect.setHeight(caretRect.height() * inverseScale);
5001 return caretRect;
5002}
5003
5004- (WebCore::FloatRect)_scaledCaretRectForSelectionEnd:(WebCore::FloatRect)caretRect
5005{
5006 // The logical height of the caret is scaled inversely by the view's zoom scale
5007 // to achieve the visual effect that the caret is narrow when zoomed in and wide
5008 // when zoomed out.
5009 double inverseScale = [self inverseScale];
5010 if (bool isHorizontalCaret = caretRect.width() < caretRect.height()) {
5011 float originalWidth = caretRect.width();
5012 caretRect.setWidth(originalWidth * inverseScale);
5013 caretRect.move(caretRect.width() - originalWidth, 0);
5014 } else {
5015 float originalHeight = caretRect.height();
5016 caretRect.setHeight(caretRect.height() * inverseScale);
5017 caretRect.move(0, caretRect.height() - originalHeight);
5018 }
5019 return caretRect;
5020}
5021
5022- (UITextRange *)selectedTextRange
5023{
5024 auto& editorState = _page->editorState();
5025 auto hasSelection = !editorState.selectionIsNone;
5026 if (!hasSelection || editorState.isMissingPostLayoutData)
5027 return nil;
5028
5029 auto isRange = editorState.selectionIsRange;
5030 auto isContentEditable = editorState.isContentEditable;
5031 // UIKit does not expect caret selections in non-editable content.
5032 if (!isContentEditable && !isRange)
5033 return nil;
5034
5035 if (_cachedSelectedTextRange)
5036 return _cachedSelectedTextRange.get();
5037
5038 auto caretStartRect = [self _scaledCaretRectForSelectionStart:_page->editorState().postLayoutData().caretRectAtStart];
5039 auto caretEndRect = [self _scaledCaretRectForSelectionEnd:_page->editorState().postLayoutData().caretRectAtEnd];
5040 auto selectionRects = textSelectionRects(_page->editorState().postLayoutData().selectionGeometries, self._contentZoomScale);
5041 auto selectedTextLength = editorState.postLayoutData().selectedTextLength;
5042 _cachedSelectedTextRange = [WKTextRange textRangeWithState:!hasSelection isRange:isRange isEditable:isContentEditable startRect:caretStartRect endRect:caretEndRect selectionRects:selectionRects selectedTextLength:selectedTextLength];
5043 return _cachedSelectedTextRange.get();
5044}

5077- (UITextRange *)markedTextRange
5078{
5079 auto& editorState = _page->editorState();
5080 bool hasComposition = editorState.hasComposition;
5081 if (!hasComposition || editorState.isMissingPostLayoutData)
5082 return nil;
5083 auto& postLayoutData = editorState.postLayoutData();
5084 auto unscaledCaretRectAtStart = postLayoutData.markedTextCaretRectAtStart;
5085 auto unscaledCaretRectAtEnd = postLayoutData.markedTextCaretRectAtEnd;
5086 auto isRange = unscaledCaretRectAtStart != unscaledCaretRectAtEnd;
5087 auto isContentEditable = editorState.isContentEditable;
5088 auto caretStartRect = [self _scaledCaretRectForSelectionStart:unscaledCaretRectAtStart];
5089 auto caretEndRect = [self _scaledCaretRectForSelectionEnd:unscaledCaretRectAtEnd];
5090 auto selectionRects = textSelectionRects(postLayoutData.markedTextRects, self._contentZoomScale);
5091 auto selectedTextLength = postLayoutData.markedText.length();
5092 return [WKTextRange textRangeWithState:!hasComposition isRange:isRange isEditable:isContentEditable startRect:caretStartRect endRect:caretEndRect selectionRects:selectionRects selectedTextLength:selectedTextLength];
5093}

5104static Vector<WebCore::CompositionHighlight> compositionHighlights(NSAttributedString *string)
5105{
5106 if (!string.length)
5107 return { };
5108
5109 Vector<WebCore::CompositionHighlight> highlights;
5110 [string enumerateAttributesInRange:NSMakeRange(0, string.length) options:0 usingBlock:[&highlights](NSDictionary<NSAttributedStringKey, id> *attributes, NSRange range, BOOL *) {
5111 if (!attributes[NSMarkedClauseSegmentAttributeName])
5112 return;
5113
5114 WebCore::Color highlightColor { WebCore::CompositionHighlight::defaultCompositionFillColor };
5115 if (UIColor *uiColor = attributes[NSBackgroundColorAttributeName])
5116 highlightColor = WebCore::colorFromUIColor(uiColor);
5117 highlights.append({ static_cast<unsigned>(range.location), static_cast<unsigned>(NSMaxRange(range)), highlightColor });
5118 }];
5119
5120 std::sort(highlights.begin(), highlights.end(), [](auto& a, auto& b) {
5121 if (a.startOffset < b.startOffset)
5122 return true;
5123 if (a.startOffset > b.startOffset)
5124 return false;
5125 return a.endOffset < b.endOffset;
5126 });
5127
5128 Vector<WebCore::CompositionHighlight> mergedHighlights;
5129 mergedHighlights.reserveInitialCapacity(highlights.size());
5130 for (auto& highlight : highlights) {
5131 if (mergedHighlights.isEmpty() || mergedHighlights.last().color != highlight.color)
5132 mergedHighlights.append(highlight);
5133 else
5134 mergedHighlights.last().endOffset = highlight.endOffset;
5135 }
5136
5137 return mergedHighlights;
5138}
5139

5142 [self _setMarkedText:markedText.string highlights:compositionHighlights(markedText) selectedRange:selectedRange];
5143}

5220static WebKit::WritingDirection coreWritingDirection(NSWritingDirection direction)
5221{
5222 switch (direction) {
5223 case NSWritingDirectionNatural:
5224 return WebCore::WritingDirection::Natural;
5225 case NSWritingDirectionLeftToRight:
5226 return WebCore::WritingDirection::LeftToRight;
5227 case NSWritingDirectionRightToLeft:
5228 return WebCore::WritingDirection::RightToLeft;
5229 default:
5230 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
5231 return WebCore::WritingDirection::Natural;
5232 }
5233}

5288// Inserts the given string, replacing any selected or marked text.
5289- (void)insertText:(NSString *)aStringValue
5290{
5291 auto* keyboard = [UIKeyboardImpl sharedInstance];
5292
5293 WebKit::InsertTextOptions options;
5294 options.processingUserGesture = keyboard.isCallingInputDelegate;
5295 options.shouldSimulateKeyboardInput = [self _shouldSimulateKeyboardInputOnTextInsertion];
5296 _page->insertTextAsync(aStringValue, WebKit::EditingRange(), WTFMove(options));
5297
5298 if (_focusedElementInformation.autocapitalizeType == WebCore::AutocapitalizeType::Words && aStringValue.length) {
5299 _lastInsertedCharacterToOverrideCharacterBeforeSelection = [aStringValue characterAtIndex:aStringValue.length - 1];
5300 _page->scheduleFullEditorStateUpdate();
5301 }
5302}
5303
5304- (void)insertText:(NSString *)aStringValue alternatives:(NSArray<NSString *> *)alternatives style:(UITextAlternativeStyle)style
5305{
5306 if (!alternatives.count)
5307 [self insertText:aStringValue];
5308 else {
5309 BOOL isLowConfidence = style == UITextAlternativeStyleLowConfidence;
5310 auto textAlternatives = adoptNS([[NSTextAlternatives alloc] initWithPrimaryString:aStringValue alternativeStrings:alternatives isLowConfidence:isLowConfidence]);
5311 WebCore::TextAlternativeWithRange textAlternativeWithRange { textAlternatives.get(), NSMakeRange(0, aStringValue.length) };
5312
5313 WebKit::InsertTextOptions options;
5314 options.shouldSimulateKeyboardInput = [self _shouldSimulateKeyboardInputOnTextInsertion];
5315 _page->insertDictatedTextAsync(aStringValue, { }, { textAlternativeWithRange }, WTFMove(options));
5316 }
5317}

5429// UITextInputPrivate protocol
5430// Direct access to the (private) UITextInputTraits object.
5431- (UITextInputTraits *)textInputTraits
5432{
5433 if (!_traits)
5434 _traits = adoptNS([[UITextInputTraits alloc] init]);
5435
5436#if USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
5437 // Do not change traits when dismissing the keyboard.
5438 if (_isBlurringFocusedElement)
5439 return _traits.get();
5440#endif
5441
5442 [self _updateTextInputTraits:_traits.get()];
5443 return _traits.get();
5444}
5445
5446- (void)_updateTextInputTraits:(id <UITextInputTraits>)traits
5447{
5448 traits.secureTextEntry = _focusedElementInformation.elementType == WebKit::InputType::Password || [_formInputSession forceSecureTextEntry];
5449
5450 switch (_focusedElementInformation.enterKeyHint) {
5451 case WebCore::EnterKeyHint::Enter:
5452 traits.returnKeyType = UIReturnKeyDefault;
5453 break;
5454 case WebCore::EnterKeyHint::Done:
5455 traits.returnKeyType = UIReturnKeyDone;
5456 break;
5457 case WebCore::EnterKeyHint::Go:
5458 traits.returnKeyType = UIReturnKeyGo;
5459 break;
5460 case WebCore::EnterKeyHint::Next:
5461 traits.returnKeyType = UIReturnKeyNext;
5462 break;
5463 case WebCore::EnterKeyHint::Search:
5464 traits.returnKeyType = UIReturnKeySearch;
5465 break;
5466 case WebCore::EnterKeyHint::Send:
5467 traits.returnKeyType = UIReturnKeySend;
5468 break;
5469 default: {
5470 if (!_focusedElementInformation.formAction.isEmpty())
5471 traits.returnKeyType = _focusedElementInformation.elementType == WebKit::InputType::Search ? UIReturnKeySearch : UIReturnKeyGo;
5472 }
5473 }
5474
5475 BOOL disableAutocorrectAndAutocapitalize = _focusedElementInformation.elementType == WebKit::InputType::Password || _focusedElementInformation.elementType == WebKit::InputType::Email
5476 || _focusedElementInformation.elementType == WebKit::InputType::URL || _focusedElementInformation.formAction.contains("login");
5477 if ([traits respondsToSelector:@selector(setAutocapitalizationType:)])
5478 traits.autocapitalizationType = disableAutocorrectAndAutocapitalize ? UITextAutocapitalizationTypeNone : toUITextAutocapitalize(_focusedElementInformation.autocapitalizeType);
5479 if ([traits respondsToSelector:@selector(setAutocorrectionType:)])
5480 traits.autocorrectionType = disableAutocorrectAndAutocapitalize ? UITextAutocorrectionTypeNo : (_focusedElementInformation.isAutocorrect ? UITextAutocorrectionTypeYes : UITextAutocorrectionTypeNo);
5481
5482 if (!_focusedElementInformation.isSpellCheckingEnabled) {
5483 if ([traits respondsToSelector:@selector(setSmartQuotesType:)])
5484 traits.smartQuotesType = UITextSmartQuotesTypeNo;
5485 if ([traits respondsToSelector:@selector(setSmartDashesType:)])
5486 traits.smartDashesType = UITextSmartDashesTypeNo;
5487 }
5488
5489 switch (_focusedElementInformation.inputMode) {
5490 case WebCore::InputMode::None:
5491 case WebCore::InputMode::Unspecified:
5492 switch (_focusedElementInformation.elementType) {
5493 case WebKit::InputType::Phone:
5494 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypePhonePad;
5495 break;
5496 case WebKit::InputType::URL:
5497 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeURL;
5498 break;
5499 case WebKit::InputType::Email:
5500 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeEmailAddress;
5501 break;
5502 case WebKit::InputType::Number:
5503 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeNumbersAndPunctuation;
5504 break;
5505 case WebKit::InputType::NumberPad:
5506 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeNumberPad;
5507 break;
5508 case WebKit::InputType::None:
5509 case WebKit::InputType::ContentEditable:
5510 case WebKit::InputType::Text:
5511 case WebKit::InputType::Password:
5512 case WebKit::InputType::TextArea:
5513 case WebKit::InputType::Search:
5514 case WebKit::InputType::Date:
5515 case WebKit::InputType::DateTimeLocal:
5516 case WebKit::InputType::Month:
5517 case WebKit::InputType::Week:
5518 case WebKit::InputType::Time:
5519 case WebKit::InputType::Select:
5520 case WebKit::InputType::Drawing:
5521#if ENABLE(INPUT_TYPE_COLOR)
5522 case WebKit::InputType::Color:
5523#endif
5524 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeDefault;
5525 }
5526 break;
5527 case WebCore::InputMode::Text:
5528 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeDefault;
5529 break;
5530 case WebCore::InputMode::Telephone:
5531 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypePhonePad;
5532 break;
5533 case WebCore::InputMode::Url:
5534 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeURL;
5535 break;
5536 case WebCore::InputMode::Email:
5537 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeEmailAddress;
5538 break;
5539 case WebCore::InputMode::Numeric:
5540 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeNumberPad;
5541 break;
5542 case WebCore::InputMode::Decimal:
5543 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeDecimalPad;
5544 break;
5545 case WebCore::InputMode::Search:
5546 traits.keyboardType = UIKeyboardTypeWebSearch;
5547 break;
5548 }
5549
5550#if HAVE(PEPPER_UI_CORE)
5551 traits.textContentType = self.textContentTypeForQuickboard;
5552#else
5553 traits.textContentType = contentTypeFromFieldName(_focusedElementInformation.autofillFieldName);
5554#endif
5555
5556 auto privateTraits = (id <UITextInputTraits_Private>)traits;
5557 if ([privateTraits respondsToSelector:@selector(setIsSingleLineDocument:)]) {
5558 switch (_focusedElementInformation.elementType) {
5559 case WebKit::InputType::ContentEditable:
5560 case WebKit::InputType::TextArea:
5561 privateTraits.isSingleLineDocument = NO;
5562 break;
5563#if ENABLE(INPUT_TYPE_COLOR)
5564 case WebKit::InputType::Color:
5565#endif
5566 case WebKit::InputType::Date:
5567 case WebKit::InputType::DateTimeLocal:
5568 case WebKit::InputType::Drawing:
5569 case WebKit::InputType::Email:
5570 case WebKit::InputType::Month:
5571 case WebKit::InputType::Number:
5572 case WebKit::InputType::NumberPad:
5573 case WebKit::InputType::Password:
5574 case WebKit::InputType::Phone:
5575 case WebKit::InputType::Search:
5576 case WebKit::InputType::Select:
5577 case WebKit::InputType::Text:
5578 case WebKit::InputType::Time:
5579 case WebKit::InputType::URL:
5580 case WebKit::InputType::Week:
5581 privateTraits.isSingleLineDocument = YES;
5582 break;
5583 case WebKit::InputType::None:
5584 break;
5585 }
5586 }
5587
5588 if ([privateTraits respondsToSelector:@selector(setShortcutConversionType:)])
5589 privateTraits.shortcutConversionType = _focusedElementInformation.elementType == WebKit::InputType::Password ? UITextShortcutConversionTypeNo : UITextShortcutConversionTypeDefault;
5590
5591 if ([traits isKindOfClass:UITextInputTraits.class])
5592 [self _updateInteractionTintColor:(UITextInputTraits *)traits];
5593}

5644- (BOOL)_isTextInputContextFocused:(_WKTextInputContext *)context
5645{
5646 ASSERT(context);
5647 // We ignore bounding rect changes as the bounding rect of the focused element is not kept up-to-date.
5648 return self._hasFocusedElement && context._textInputContext.isSameElement(_focusedElementInformation.elementContext);
5649}
5650
5651- (void)_focusTextInputContext:(_WKTextInputContext *)context placeCaretAt:(CGPoint)point completionHandler:(void (^)(UIResponder<UITextInput> *))completionHandler
5652{
5653 ASSERT(context);
5654 // This function can be called more than once during a text interaction (e.g. <rdar://problem/59430806>).
5655 if (![self becomeFirstResponder]) {
5656 completionHandler(nil);
5657 return;
5658 }
5659 if ([self _isTextInputContextFocused:context]) {
5660 completionHandler(_focusedElementInformation.isReadOnly ? nil : self);
5661 return;
5662 }
5663 _usingGestureForSelection = YES;
5664 auto checkFocusedElement = [weakSelf = WeakObjCPtr<WKContentView> { self }, context = adoptNS([context copy]), completionHandler = makeBlockPtr(completionHandler)] (bool success) {
5665 auto strongSelf = weakSelf.get();
5666 if (!strongSelf) {
5667 completionHandler(nil);
5668 return;
5669 }
5670 bool isFocused = success && [strongSelf _isTextInputContextFocused:context.get()];
5671 bool isEditable = success && !strongSelf->_focusedElementInformation.isReadOnly;
5672 strongSelf->_textInteractionDidChangeFocusedElement |= isFocused;
5673 strongSelf->_usingGestureForSelection = NO;
5674 completionHandler(isFocused && isEditable ? strongSelf.get() : nil);
5675 };
5676 _page->focusTextInputContextAndPlaceCaret(context._textInputContext, WebCore::IntPoint { point }, WTFMove(checkFocusedElement));
5677}
5678
5679- (void)_requestTextInputContextsInRect:(CGRect)rect completionHandler:(void (^)(NSArray<_WKTextInputContext *> *))completionHandler
5680{
5681 WebCore::FloatRect searchRect { rect };
5682#if ENABLE(EDITABLE_REGION)
5683 bool hitInteractionRect = self._hasFocusedElement && searchRect.inclusivelyIntersects(_focusedElementInformation.interactionRect);
5684 if (!self.webView._editable && !hitInteractionRect && !WebKit::mayContainEditableElementsInRect(self, rect)) {
5685 completionHandler(@[ ]);
5686 return;
5687 }
5688#endif
5689 _page->textInputContextsInRect(searchRect, [weakSelf = WeakObjCPtr<WKContentView>(self), completionHandler = makeBlockPtr(completionHandler)] (const Vector<WebCore::ElementContext>& contexts) {
5690 auto strongSelf = weakSelf.get();
5691 if (!strongSelf || contexts.isEmpty()) {
5692 completionHandler(@[ ]);
5693 return;
5694 }
5695 completionHandler(createNSArray(contexts, [] (const auto& context) {
5696 return adoptNS([[_WKTextInputContext alloc] _initWithTextInputContext:context]);
5697 }).get());
5698 });
5699}
5700
5701- (void)_willBeginTextInteractionInTextInputContext:(_WKTextInputContext *)context
5702{
5703 ASSERT(context);
5704
5705 _page->setCanShowPlaceholder(context._textInputContext, false);
5706
5707 ++_activeTextInteractionCount;
5708 if (_activeTextInteractionCount > 1)
5709 return;
5710
5711 _textInteractionDidChangeFocusedElement = NO;
5712 _page->setShouldRevealCurrentSelectionAfterInsertion(false);
5713 _usingGestureForSelection = YES;
5714}
5715
5716- (void)_didFinishTextInteractionInTextInputContext:(_WKTextInputContext *)context
5717{
5718 ASSERT(context);
5719
5720 _page->setCanShowPlaceholder(context._textInputContext, true);
5721
5722 ASSERT(_activeTextInteractionCount > 0);
5723 --_activeTextInteractionCount;
5724 if (_activeTextInteractionCount)
5725 return;
5726
5727 _usingGestureForSelection = NO;
5728
5729 if (_textInteractionDidChangeFocusedElement) {
5730 // Mark to zoom to reveal the newly focused element on the next editor state update.
5731 // Then tell the web process to reveal the current selection, which will send us (the
5732 // UI process) an editor state update.
5733 _page->setWaitingForPostLayoutEditorStateUpdateAfterFocusingElement(true);
5734 _textInteractionDidChangeFocusedElement = NO;
5735 }
5736
5737 _page->setShouldRevealCurrentSelectionAfterInsertion(true);
5738}

5740#if USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
5741
5742- (void)modifierFlagsDidChangeFrom:(UIKeyModifierFlags)oldFlags to:(UIKeyModifierFlags)newFlags
5743{
5744 auto dispatchSyntheticFlagsChangedEvents = [&] (UIKeyModifierFlags flags, bool keyDown) {
5745 if (flags & UIKeyModifierShift)
5746 [self handleKeyWebEvent:adoptNS([[WKSyntheticFlagsChangedWebEvent alloc] initWithShiftState:keyDown]).get()];
5747 if (flags & UIKeyModifierAlphaShift)
5748 [self handleKeyWebEvent:adoptNS([[WKSyntheticFlagsChangedWebEvent alloc] initWithCapsLockState:keyDown]).get()];
5749 };
5750
5751 UIKeyModifierFlags removedFlags = oldFlags & ~newFlags;
5752 UIKeyModifierFlags addedFlags = newFlags & ~oldFlags;
5753 if (removedFlags)
5754 dispatchSyntheticFlagsChangedEvents(removedFlags, false);
5755 if (addedFlags)
5756 dispatchSyntheticFlagsChangedEvents(addedFlags, true);
5757}

5772- (void)_handleKeyUIEvent:(::UIEvent *)event
5773{
5774 bool isHardwareKeyboardEvent = !!event._hidEvent;
5775 // We only want to handle key event from the hardware keyboard when we are
5776 // first responder and we are not interacting with editable content.
5777 if ([self isFirstResponder] && isHardwareKeyboardEvent && (_inputPeripheral || !_page->editorState().isContentEditable)) {
5778 if ([_inputPeripheral respondsToSelector:@selector(handleKeyEvent:)]) {
5779 if ([_inputPeripheral handleKeyEvent:event])
5780 return;
5781 }
5782#if USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
5783 if (!_seenHardwareKeyDownInNonEditableElement) {
5784 _seenHardwareKeyDownInNonEditableElement = YES;
5785 [self reloadInputViews];
5786 }
5787 [super _handleKeyUIEvent:event];
5788#else
5789 [self handleKeyEvent:event];
5790#endif
5791 return;
5792 }
5793
5794 [super _handleKeyUIEvent:event];
5795}

5801
5802#if !USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
5803- (void)handleKeyEvent:(::UIEvent *)event
5804{
5805 // WebCore has already seen the event, no need for custom processing.
5806 if (event == _uiEventBeingResent)
5807 return;
5808
5809 auto webEvent = adoptNS([[WKWebEvent alloc] initWithEvent:event]);
5810
5811 [self handleKeyWebEvent:webEvent.get()];
5812}
5813#endif
5814
5815- (void)handleKeyWebEvent:(::WebEvent *)theEvent
5816{
5817 _page->handleKeyboardEvent(WebKit::NativeWebKeyboardEvent(theEvent, WebKit::NativeWebKeyboardEvent::HandledByInputMethod::No));
5818}
5819
5820- (void)handleKeyWebEvent:(::WebEvent *)theEvent withCompletionHandler:(void (^)(::WebEvent *theEvent, BOOL wasHandled))completionHandler
5821{
5822 if (!isUIThread()) {
5823 RELEASE_LOG_FAULT(KeyHandling, "%s was invoked on a background thread.", __PRETTY_FUNCTION__);
5824 completionHandler(theEvent, NO);
5825 return;
5826 }
5827
5828 [self _handleDOMPasteRequestWithResult:WebCore::DOMPasteAccessResponse::DeniedForGesture];
5829
5830 using HandledByInputMethod = WebKit::NativeWebKeyboardEvent::HandledByInputMethod;
5831#if USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
5832 auto* keyboard = [UIKeyboardImpl sharedInstance];
5833 if ((_page->editorState().isContentEditable || _treatAsContentEditableUntilNextEditorStateUpdate) && [keyboard handleKeyInputMethodCommandForCurrentEvent]) {
5834 completionHandler(theEvent, YES);
5835 _page->handleKeyboardEvent(WebKit::NativeWebKeyboardEvent(theEvent, HandledByInputMethod::Yes));
5836 return;
5837 }
5838#endif
5839 if (_page->handleKeyboardEvent(WebKit::NativeWebKeyboardEvent(theEvent, HandledByInputMethod::No)))
5840 _keyWebEventHandler = makeBlockPtr(completionHandler);
5841 else
5842 completionHandler(theEvent, NO);
5843}
5844
5845- (void)_didHandleKeyEvent:(::WebEvent *)event eventWasHandled:(BOOL)eventWasHandled
5846{
5847#if USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
5848 if ([event isKindOfClass:[WKSyntheticFlagsChangedWebEvent class]])
5849 return;
5850#endif
5851
5852 if (!(event.keyboardFlags & WebEventKeyboardInputModifierFlagsChanged))
5853 [_keyboardScrollingAnimator handleKeyEvent:event];
5854
5855 if (auto handler = WTFMove(_keyWebEventHandler)) {
5856 handler(event, eventWasHandled);
5857 return;
5858 }
5859
5860#if !USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
5861 // If we aren't interacting with editable content, we still need to call [super _handleKeyUIEvent:]
5862 // so that keyboard repeat will work correctly. If we are interacting with editable content,
5863 // we already did so in _handleKeyUIEvent.
5864 if (eventWasHandled && _page->editorState().isContentEditable)
5865 return;
5866
5867 if (![event isKindOfClass:[WKWebEvent class]])
5868 return;
5869
5870 // Resending the event may destroy this WKContentView.
5871 RetainPtr<WKContentView> protector(self);
5872
5873 // We keep here the event when resending it to the application to distinguish
5874 // the case of a new event from one that has been already sent to WebCore.
5875 ASSERT(!_uiEventBeingResent);
5876 _uiEventBeingResent = [(WKWebEvent *)event uiEvent];
5877 [super _handleKeyUIEvent:_uiEventBeingResent.get()];
5878 _uiEventBeingResent = nil;
5879#endif
5880}
5881
5882- (BOOL)_interpretKeyEvent:(::WebEvent *)event isCharEvent:(BOOL)isCharEvent
5883{
5884 if (event.keyboardFlags & WebEventKeyboardInputModifierFlagsChanged)
5885 return NO;
5886
5887 BOOL contentEditable = _page->editorState().isContentEditable;
5888
5889 if (!contentEditable && event.isTabKey)
5890 return NO;
5891
5892 if ([_keyboardScrollingAnimator beginWithEvent:event] || [_keyboardScrollingAnimator scrollTriggeringKeyIsPressed])
5893 return YES;
5894
5895 UIKeyboardImpl *keyboard = [UIKeyboardImpl sharedInstance];
5896
5897 if (!isCharEvent && [keyboard handleKeyTextCommandForCurrentEvent])
5898 return YES;
5899 if (isCharEvent && [keyboard handleKeyAppCommandForCurrentEvent])
5900 return YES;
5901
5902 // Don't insert character for an unhandled Command-key key command. This matches iOS and Mac platform conventions.
5903 if (event.modifierFlags & WebEventFlagMaskCommandKey)
5904 return NO;
5905
5906 NSString *characters = event.characters;
5907 if (!characters.length)
5908 return NO;
5909
5910 switch ([characters characterAtIndex:0]) {
5911 case NSBackspaceCharacter:
5912 case NSDeleteCharacter:
5913 if (contentEditable) {
5914 [keyboard deleteFromInputWithFlags:event.keyboardFlags];
5915 return YES;
5916 }
5917 break;
5918 case NSEnterCharacter:
5919 case NSCarriageReturnCharacter:
5920 if (contentEditable && isCharEvent) {
5921 // Map \r from HW keyboard to \n to match the behavior of the soft keyboard.
5922 [keyboard addInputString:@"\n" withFlags:0 withInputManagerHint:nil];
5923 return YES;
5924 }
5925 break;
5926 default:
5927 if (contentEditable && isCharEvent) {
5928 [keyboard addInputString:event.characters withFlags:event.keyboardFlags withInputManagerHint:event.inputManagerHint];
5929 return YES;
5930 }
5931 break;
5932 }
5933
5934 return NO;
5935}

5950- (BOOL)isScrollableForKeyboardScrollViewAnimator:(WKKeyboardScrollViewAnimator *)animator
5951{
5952 if (_page->editorState().isContentEditable)
5953 return NO;
5954
5955 if (_focusedElementInformation.elementType == WebKit::InputType::Select)
5956 return NO;
5957
5958 if (!self.webView.scrollView.scrollEnabled)
5959 return NO;
5960
5961 return YES;
5962}
5963
5964- (CGFloat)keyboardScrollViewAnimator:(WKKeyboardScrollViewAnimator *)animator distanceForIncrement:(WebCore::ScrollGranularity)increment inDirection:(WebCore::ScrollDirection)direction
5965{
5966 BOOL directionIsHorizontal = direction == WebCore::ScrollDirection::ScrollLeft || direction == WebCore::ScrollDirection::ScrollRight;
5967
5968 switch (increment) {
5969 case WebCore::ScrollGranularity::ScrollByDocument: {
5970 CGSize documentSize = [self convertRect:self.bounds toView:self.webView].size;
5971 return directionIsHorizontal ? documentSize.width : documentSize.height;
5972 }
5973 case WebCore::ScrollGranularity::ScrollByPage: {
5974 CGSize pageSize = [self convertSize:CGSizeMake(0, WebCore::Scrollbar::pageStep(_page->unobscuredContentRect().height(), self.bounds.size.height)) toView:self.webView];
5975 return directionIsHorizontal ? pageSize.width : pageSize.height;
5976 }
5977 case WebCore::ScrollGranularity::ScrollByLine:
5978 return [self convertSize:CGSizeMake(0, WebCore::Scrollbar::pixelsPerLineStep()) toView:self.webView].height;
5979 case WebCore::ScrollGranularity::ScrollByPixel:
5980 return 0;
5981 }
5982 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
5983 return 0;
5984}

5996- (void)executeEditCommandWithCallback:(NSString *)commandName
5997{
5998 // FIXME: Editing commands are not considered by WebKit as user initiated even if they are the result
5999 // of keydown or keyup. We need to query the keyboard to determine if this was called from the keyboard
6000 // or not to know whether to tell WebKit to treat this command as user initiated or not.
6001 [self beginSelectionChange];
6002 RetainPtr<WKContentView> view = self;
6003 _page->executeEditCommand(commandName, { }, [view] {
6004 [view endSelectionChange];
6005 });
6006}

6194- (BOOL)isPosition:(UITextPosition *)position atBoundary:(UITextGranularity)granularity inDirection:(UITextDirection)direction
6195{
6196 if (granularity == UITextGranularityParagraph) {
6197 if (direction == UITextStorageDirectionBackward && [position isEqual:self.selectedTextRange.start])
6198 return _page->editorState().postLayoutData().selectionStartIsAtParagraphBoundary;
6199
6200 if (direction == UITextStorageDirectionForward && [position isEqual:self.selectedTextRange.end])
6201 return _page->editorState().postLayoutData().selectionEndIsAtParagraphBoundary;
6202 }
6203
6204 return NO;

6275// Note that selectability is also affected by the CSS property user-select.
6276static bool mayContainSelectableText(WebKit::InputType type)
6277{
6278 switch (type) {
6279 case WebKit::InputType::None:
6280 // The following types have custom UI and do not look or behave like a text field.
6281#if ENABLE(INPUT_TYPE_COLOR)
6282 case WebKit::InputType::Color:
6283#endif
6284 case WebKit::InputType::Date:
6285 case WebKit::InputType::DateTimeLocal:
6286 case WebKit::InputType::Drawing:
6287 case WebKit::InputType::Month:
6288 case WebKit::InputType::Select:
6289 case WebKit::InputType::Time:
6290 return false;
6291 // The following types look and behave like a text field.
6292 case WebKit::InputType::ContentEditable:
6293 case WebKit::InputType::Email:
6294 case WebKit::InputType::Number:
6295 case WebKit::InputType::NumberPad:
6296 case WebKit::InputType::Password:
6297 case WebKit::InputType::Phone:
6298 case WebKit::InputType::Search:
6299 case WebKit::InputType::Text:
6300 case WebKit::InputType::TextArea:
6301 case WebKit::InputType::URL:
6302 case WebKit::InputType::Week:
6303 return true;
6304 }
6305}
6306
6307- (bool)_shouldShowKeyboardForElement:(const WebKit::FocusedElementInformation&)information
6308{
6309 if (information.inputMode == WebCore::InputMode::None)
6310 return false;
6311
6312 if (mayContainSelectableText(information.elementType))
6313 return true;
6314
6315 return [self _elementTypeRequiresAccessoryView:information.elementType];
6316}

6318static RetainPtr<NSObject <WKFormPeripheral>> createInputPeripheralWithView(WebKit::InputType type, WKContentView *view)
6319{
6320#if PLATFORM(WATCHOS)
6321 UNUSED_PARAM(type);
6322 UNUSED_PARAM(view);
6323 return nil;
6324#else
6325 switch (type) {
6326 case WebKit::InputType::Select:
6327 return adoptNS([[WKFormSelectControl alloc] initWithView:view]);
6328#if ENABLE(INPUT_TYPE_COLOR)
6329 case WebKit::InputType::Color:
6330 return adoptNS([[WKFormColorControl alloc] initWithView:view]);
6331#endif // ENABLE(INPUT_TYPE_COLOR)
6332 case WebKit::InputType::Date:
6333 case WebKit::InputType::DateTimeLocal:
6334 case WebKit::InputType::Month:
6335 case WebKit::InputType::Time:
6336 return adoptNS([[WKDateTimeInputControl alloc] initWithView:view]);
6337 default:
6338 return nil;
6339 }
6340#endif
6341}
6342
6343- (void)_elementDidFocus:(const WebKit::FocusedElementInformation&)information userIsInteracting:(BOOL)userIsInteracting blurPreviousNode:(BOOL)blurPreviousNode activityStateChanges:(OptionSet<WebCore::ActivityState::Flag>)activityStateChanges userObject:(NSObject <NSSecureCoding> *)userObject
6344{
6345 SetForScope<BOOL> isChangingFocusForScope { _isChangingFocus, self._hasFocusedElement };
6346 SetForScope<BOOL> isFocusingElementWithKeyboardForScope { _isFocusingElementWithKeyboard, [self _shouldShowKeyboardForElement:information] };
6347
6348 auto runModalJavaScriptDialogCallbackIfNeeded = makeScopeExit([&] {
6349 if (auto callback = std::exchange(_pendingRunModalJavaScriptDialogCallback, { }))
6350 callback();
6351 });
6352
6353 auto inputViewUpdateDeferrer = std::exchange(_inputViewUpdateDeferrer, nullptr);
6354
6355 _didAccessoryTabInitiateFocus = _isChangingFocusUsingAccessoryTab;
6356
6357 id <_WKInputDelegate> inputDelegate = [_webView _inputDelegate];
6358 RetainPtr<WKFocusedElementInfo> focusedElementInfo = adoptNS([[WKFocusedElementInfo alloc] initWithFocusedElementInformation:information isUserInitiated:userIsInteracting userObject:userObject]);
6359
6360 _WKFocusStartsInputSessionPolicy startInputSessionPolicy = _WKFocusStartsInputSessionPolicyAuto;
6361
6362 if ([inputDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:focusShouldStartInputSession:)]) {
6363 if ([inputDelegate _webView:self.webView focusShouldStartInputSession:focusedElementInfo.get()])
6364 startInputSessionPolicy = _WKFocusStartsInputSessionPolicyAllow;
6365 else
6366 startInputSessionPolicy = _WKFocusStartsInputSessionPolicyDisallow;
6367 }
6368
6369 if ([inputDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:decidePolicyForFocusedElement:)])
6370 startInputSessionPolicy = [inputDelegate _webView:self.webView decidePolicyForFocusedElement:focusedElementInfo.get()];
6371
6372 BOOL shouldShowInputView = [&] {
6373 switch (startInputSessionPolicy) {
6374 case _WKFocusStartsInputSessionPolicyAuto:
6375 // The default behavior is to allow node assistance if the user is interacting.
6376 // We also allow node assistance if the keyboard already is showing, unless we're in extra zoom mode.
6377 if (userIsInteracting)
6378 return YES;
6379
6380 if (self.isFirstResponder || _becomingFirstResponder) {
6381 // When the software keyboard is being used to enter an url, only the focus activity state is changing.
6382 // In this case, auto focus on the page being navigated to should be disabled, unless a hardware
6383 // keyboard is attached.
6384 if (activityStateChanges && activityStateChanges != WebCore::ActivityState::IsFocused)
6385 return YES;
6386
6387#if HAVE(PEPPER_UI_CORE)
6388 if (_isChangingFocus && ![_focusedFormControlView isHidden])
6389 return YES;
6390#else
6391 if (_isChangingFocus)
6392 return YES;
6393
6394 if (_isFocusingElementWithKeyboard && [UIKeyboard isInHardwareKeyboardMode])
6395 return YES;
6396#endif
6397 }
6398 return NO;
6399 case _WKFocusStartsInputSessionPolicyAllow:
6400 return YES;
6401 case _WKFocusStartsInputSessionPolicyDisallow:
6402 return NO;
6403 default:
6404 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
6405 return NO;
6406 }
6407 }();
6408
6409 // Do not present input peripherals if a validation message is being displayed.
6410 if (information.isFocusingWithValidationMessage && !_isFocusingElementWithKeyboard)
6411 shouldShowInputView = NO;
6412
6413 if (blurPreviousNode) {
6414 // Defer view updates until the end of this function to avoid a noticeable flash when switching focus
6415 // between elements that require the keyboard.
6416 if (!inputViewUpdateDeferrer)
6417 inputViewUpdateDeferrer = makeUnique<WebKit::InputViewUpdateDeferrer>(self);
6418 [self _elementDidBlur];
6419 }
6420
6421 if (!shouldShowInputView || information.elementType == WebKit::InputType::None) {
6422 _page->setIsShowingInputViewForFocusedElement(false);
6423 return;
6424 }
6425
6426 _page->setIsShowingInputViewForFocusedElement(true);
6427
6428 // FIXME: We should remove this check when we manage to send ElementDidFocus from the WebProcess
6429 // only when it is truly time to show the keyboard.
6430 if (_focusedElementInformation.elementType == information.elementType && _focusedElementInformation.interactionRect == information.interactionRect) {
6431 if (_inputPeripheral) {
6432 if (!self.isFirstResponder)
6433 [self becomeFirstResponder];
6434 [self accessoryOpen];
6435 }
6436 return;
6437 }
6438
6439 [_webView _resetFocusPreservationCount];
6440
6441 _focusRequiresStrongPasswordAssistance = NO;
6442 _additionalContextForStrongPasswordAssistance = nil;
6443 if ([inputDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:focusRequiresStrongPasswordAssistance:)])
6444 _focusRequiresStrongPasswordAssistance = [inputDelegate _webView:self.webView focusRequiresStrongPasswordAssistance:focusedElementInfo.get()];
6445
6446 if ([inputDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webViewAdditionalContextForStrongPasswordAssistance:)])
6447 _additionalContextForStrongPasswordAssistance = [inputDelegate _webViewAdditionalContextForStrongPasswordAssistance:self.webView];
6448 else
6449 _additionalContextForStrongPasswordAssistance = @{ };
6450
6451 bool delegateImplementsWillStartInputSession = [inputDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:willStartInputSession:)];
6452 bool delegateImplementsDidStartInputSession = [inputDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:didStartInputSession:)];
6453
6454 if (delegateImplementsWillStartInputSession || delegateImplementsDidStartInputSession) {
6455 [_formInputSession invalidate];
6456 _formInputSession = adoptNS([[WKFormInputSession alloc] initWithContentView:self focusedElementInfo:focusedElementInfo.get() requiresStrongPasswordAssistance:_focusRequiresStrongPasswordAssistance]);
6457 }
6458
6459 if (delegateImplementsWillStartInputSession)
6460 [inputDelegate _webView:self.webView willStartInputSession:_formInputSession.get()];
6461
6462 BOOL isSelectable = mayContainSelectableText(information.elementType);
6463 BOOL editableChanged = [self setIsEditable:isSelectable];
6464 _focusedElementInformation = information;
6465 _traits = nil;
6466
6467 if (![self isFirstResponder])
6468 [self becomeFirstResponder];
6469
6470 if (!_suppressSelectionAssistantReasons && isSelectable && activityStateChanges.contains(WebCore::ActivityState::IsFocused)) {
6471 _treatAsContentEditableUntilNextEditorStateUpdate = YES;
6472 [_textInteractionAssistant activateSelection];
6473 _page->restoreSelectionInFocusedEditableElement();
6474 _page->scheduleFullEditorStateUpdate();
6475 }
6476
6477 _inputPeripheral = createInputPeripheralWithView(_focusedElementInformation.elementType, self);
6478
6479#if HAVE(PEPPER_UI_CORE)
6480 [self addFocusedFormControlOverlay];
6481 if (!_isChangingFocus)
6482 [self presentViewControllerForCurrentFocusedElement];
6483#else
6484 [self reloadInputViews];
6485#endif
6486
6487 if (isSelectable) {
6488 [self _showKeyboard];
6489 if (!self.window.keyWindow)
6490 [self.window makeKeyWindow];
6491 }
6492
6493 // The custom fixed position rect behavior is affected by -isFocusingElement, so if that changes we need to recompute rects.
6494 if (editableChanged)
6495 [_webView _scheduleVisibleContentRectUpdate];
6496
6497 // For elements that have selectable content (e.g. text field) we need to wait for the web process to send an up-to-date
6498 // selection rect before we can zoom and reveal the selection. Non-selectable elements (e.g. <select>) can be zoomed
6499 // immediately because they have no selection to reveal.
6500 BOOL needsEditorStateUpdate = mayContainSelectableText(_focusedElementInformation.elementType);
6501 if (needsEditorStateUpdate)
6502 _page->setWaitingForPostLayoutEditorStateUpdateAfterFocusingElement(true);
6503 else
6504 [self _zoomToRevealFocusedElement];
6505
6506 [self _updateAccessory];
6507
6508#if HAVE(PEPPER_UI_CORE)
6509 if (_isChangingFocus)
6510 [_focusedFormControlView reloadData:YES];
6511#endif
6512
6513 // _inputPeripheral has been initialized in inputView called by reloadInputViews.
6514 [_inputPeripheral beginEditing];
6515
6516 if (delegateImplementsDidStartInputSession)
6517 [inputDelegate _webView:self.webView didStartInputSession:_formInputSession.get()];
6518
6519 [_webView didStartFormControlInteraction];
6520}
6521
6522- (void)_elementDidBlur
6523{
6524 SetForScope<BOOL> isBlurringFocusedElementForScope { _isBlurringFocusedElement, YES };
6525
6526#if USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
6527 [self _endEditing];
6528#endif
6529
6530 [_formInputSession invalidate];
6531 _formInputSession = nil;
6532
6533#if ENABLE(DATALIST_ELEMENT)
6534 _dataListTextSuggestionsInputView = nil;
6535 _dataListTextSuggestions = nil;
6536#endif
6537
6538 BOOL editableChanged = [self setIsEditable:NO];
6539 // FIXME: We should completely invalidate _focusedElementInformation here, instead of a subset of individual members.
6540 _focusedElementInformation.elementType = WebKit::InputType::None;
6541 _focusedElementInformation.shouldSynthesizeKeyEventsForEditing = false;
6542 _focusedElementInformation.shouldAvoidResizingWhenInputViewBoundsChange = false;
6543 _focusedElementInformation.shouldAvoidScrollingWhenFocusedContentIsVisible = false;
6544 _focusedElementInformation.shouldUseLegacySelectPopoverDismissalBehaviorInDataActivation = false;
6545 _focusedElementInformation.isFocusingWithValidationMessage = false;
6546 _inputPeripheral = nil;
6547 _focusRequiresStrongPasswordAssistance = NO;
6548 _additionalContextForStrongPasswordAssistance = nil;
6549
6550#if USE(UIKIT_KEYBOARD_ADDITIONS)
6551 // When defocusing an editable element reset a seen keydown before calling -_hideKeyboard so that we
6552 // re-evaluate whether we still need a keyboard when UIKit calls us back in -_requiresKeyboardWhenFirstResponder.
6553 if (editableChanged)
6554 _seenHardwareKeyDownInNonEditableElement = NO;
6555#endif
6556
6557 [self _hideKeyboard];
6558
6559#if HAVE(PEPPER_UI_CORE)
6560 [self dismissAllInputViewControllers:YES];
6561 if (!_isChangingFocus)
6562 [self removeFocusedFormControlOverlay];
6563#endif
6564
6565 if (editableChanged) {
6566 // The custom fixed position rect behavior is affected by -isFocusingElement, so if that changes we need to recompute rects.
6567 [_webView _scheduleVisibleContentRectUpdate];
6568
6569 [_webView didEndFormControlInteraction];
6570 _page->setIsShowingInputViewForFocusedElement(false);
6571 }
6572
6573 _page->setWaitingForPostLayoutEditorStateUpdateAfterFocusingElement(false);
6574
6575 if (!_isChangingFocus)
6576 _didAccessoryTabInitiateFocus = NO;
6577
6578 _lastInsertedCharacterToOverrideCharacterBeforeSelection = std::nullopt;
6579}
6580
6581- (void)_updateInputContextAfterBlurringAndRefocusingElement
6582{
6583 if (!self._hasFocusedElement || !_suppressSelectionAssistantReasons)
6584 return;
6585
6586 [UIKeyboardImpl.activeInstance updateForChangedSelection];
6587}

6594 if (UIPeripheralHost.sharedInstance.rotationState)
6595 return YES;
6596
6597 if (_isChangingFocus && _isFocusingElementWithKeyboard)
6598 return YES;
6599
6600 return NO;

6621
6622static BOOL allPasteboardItemOriginsMatchOrigin(UIPasteboard *pasteboard, const String& originIdentifier)
6623{
6624 if (originIdentifier.isEmpty())
6625 return NO;
6626
6627 auto *indices = [NSIndexSet indexSetWithIndexesInRange:NSMakeRange(0, [pasteboard numberOfItems])];
6628 auto *allCustomData = [pasteboard dataForPasteboardType:@(WebCore::PasteboardCustomData::cocoaType()) inItemSet:indices];
6629 if (!allCustomData.count)
6630 return NO;
6631
6632 BOOL foundAtLeastOneMatchingIdentifier = NO;
6633 for (NSData *data in allCustomData) {
6634 if (!data.length)
6635 continue;
6636
6637 auto buffer = WebCore::SharedBuffer::create(data);
6638 if (WebCore::PasteboardCustomData::fromSharedBuffer(buffer.get()).origin() != originIdentifier)
6639 return NO;
6640
6641 foundAtLeastOneMatchingIdentifier = YES;
6642 }
6643
6644 return foundAtLeastOneMatchingIdentifier;
6645}
6646
6647- (void)_requestDOMPasteAccessWithElementRect:(const WebCore::IntRect&)elementRect originIdentifier:(const String&)originIdentifier completionHandler:(CompletionHandler<void(WebCore::DOMPasteAccessResponse)>&&)completionHandler
6648{
6649 if (auto existingCompletionHandler = std::exchange(_domPasteRequestHandler, WTFMove(completionHandler))) {
6650 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
6651 existingCompletionHandler(WebCore::DOMPasteAccessResponse::DeniedForGesture);
6652 }
6653
6654 if (allPasteboardItemOriginsMatchOrigin(UIPasteboard.generalPasteboard, originIdentifier)) {
6655 [self _handleDOMPasteRequestWithResult:WebCore::DOMPasteAccessResponse::GrantedForCommand];
6656 return;
6657 }
6658
6659 WebCore::IntRect menuControllerRect = elementRect;
6660
6661 const CGFloat maximumElementWidth = 300;
6662 const CGFloat maximumElementHeight = 120;
6663 if (elementRect.isEmpty() || elementRect.width() > maximumElementWidth || elementRect.height() > maximumElementHeight) {
6664 const CGFloat interactionLocationMargin = 10;
6665 menuControllerRect = { WebCore::IntPoint(_lastInteractionLocation), { } };
6666 menuControllerRect.inflate(interactionLocationMargin);
6667 }
6668
6669 [UIMenuController.sharedMenuController showMenuFromView:self rect:menuControllerRect];
6670}

6672- (void)doAfterEditorStateUpdateAfterFocusingElement:(dispatch_block_t)block
6673{
6674 if (!_page->waitingForPostLayoutEditorStateUpdateAfterFocusingElement()) {
6675 block();
6676 return;
6677 }
6678
6679 _actionsToPerformAfterEditorStateUpdate.append(makeBlockPtr(block));
6680}

6682- (void)_didUpdateEditorState
6683{
6684 [self _updateInitialWritingDirectionIfNecessary];
6685
6686 // FIXME: If the initial writing direction just changed, we should wait until we get the next post-layout editor state
6687 // before zooming to reveal the selection rect.
6688 if (mayContainSelectableText(_focusedElementInformation.elementType))
6689 [self _zoomToRevealFocusedElement];
6690
6691 _treatAsContentEditableUntilNextEditorStateUpdate = NO;
6692
6693 for (auto block : std::exchange(_actionsToPerformAfterEditorStateUpdate, { }))
6694 block();
6695}
6696
6697- (void)_updateInitialWritingDirectionIfNecessary
6698{
6699 if (!_page->isEditable())
6700 return;
6701
6702 auto& editorState = _page->editorState();
6703 if (editorState.selectionIsNone || editorState.selectionIsRange)
6704 return;
6705
6706 UIKeyboardImpl *keyboard = UIKeyboardImpl.activeInstance;
6707 if (keyboard.delegate != self)
6708 return;
6709
6710 // Synchronize the keyboard's writing direction with the newly received EditorState.
6711 [keyboard setInitialDirection];
6712}

6714- (void)updateCurrentFocusedElementInformation:(Function<void(bool didUpdate)>&&)callback
6715{
6716 WeakObjCPtr<WKContentView> weakSelf { self };
6717 auto identifierBeforeUpdate = _focusedElementInformation.focusedElementIdentifier;
6718 _page->requestFocusedElementInformation([callback = WTFMove(callback), identifierBeforeUpdate, weakSelf] (auto& info) {
6719 if (!weakSelf || !info || info->focusedElementIdentifier != identifierBeforeUpdate) {
6720 // If the focused element may have changed in the meantime, don't overwrite focused element information.
6721 callback(false);
6722 return;
6723 }
6724
6725 weakSelf.get()->_focusedElementInformation = info.value();
6726 callback(true);
6727 });
6728}

6792static bool canUseQuickboardControllerFor(UITextContentType type)
6793{
6794 return [type isEqualToString:UITextContentTypeUsername] || [type isEqualToString:UITextContentTypePassword] || [type isEqualToString:UITextContentTypeEmailAddress];

6798
6799- (void)presentViewControllerForCurrentFocusedElement
6800{
6801 [self dismissAllInputViewControllers:NO];
6802
6803 _shouldRestoreFirstResponderStatusAfterLosingFocus = self.isFirstResponder;
6804 UIViewController *presentingViewController = [UIViewController _viewControllerForFullScreenPresentationFromView:self];
6805
6806 ASSERT(!_presentedFullScreenInputViewController);
6807
6808 BOOL prefersModalPresentation = NO;
6809
6810 switch (_focusedElementInformation.elementType) {
6811 case WebKit::InputType::Select:
6812 _presentedFullScreenInputViewController = adoptNS([[WKSelectMenuListViewController alloc] initWithDelegate:self]);
6813 break;
6814 case WebKit::InputType::Time:
6815 // Time inputs are special, in that the only UI affordances for dismissal are push buttons rather than status bar chevrons.
6816 // As such, modal presentation and dismissal is preferred even if a navigation stack exists.
6817 prefersModalPresentation = YES;
6818 _presentedFullScreenInputViewController = adoptNS([[WKTimePickerViewController alloc] initWithDelegate:self]);
6819 break;
6820 case WebKit::InputType::Date:
6821 _presentedFullScreenInputViewController = adoptNS([[WKDatePickerViewController alloc] initWithDelegate:self]);
6822 break;
6823 case WebKit::InputType::None:
6824 break;
6825 default: {
6826#if HAVE(QUICKBOARD_CONTROLLER)
6827 if (canUseQuickboardControllerFor(self.textContentTypeForQuickboard)) {
6828 _presentedQuickboardController = [self _createQuickboardController:presentingViewController];
6829 break;
6830 }
6831#endif
6832 _presentedFullScreenInputViewController = adoptNS([[WKTextInputListViewController alloc] initWithDelegate:self]);
6833 break;
6834 }
6835 }
6836
6837#if HAVE(QUICKBOARD_CONTROLLER)
6838 ASSERT_IMPLIES(_presentedQuickboardController, !_presentedFullScreenInputViewController);
6839 ASSERT_IMPLIES(_presentedFullScreenInputViewController, !_presentedQuickboardController);
6840#endif // HAVE(QUICKBOARD_CONTROLLER)
6841 ASSERT(self._isPresentingFullScreenInputView);
6842 ASSERT(presentingViewController);
6843
6844 if (!prefersModalPresentation && [presentingViewController isKindOfClass:[UINavigationController class]])
6845 _inputNavigationViewControllerForFullScreenInputs = (UINavigationController *)presentingViewController;
6846 else
6847 _inputNavigationViewControllerForFullScreenInputs = nil;
6848
6849 RetainPtr<UIViewController> controller;
6850 if (_presentedFullScreenInputViewController) {
6851 // Present the input view controller on an existing navigation stack, if possible. If there is no navigation stack we can use, fall back to presenting modally.
6852 // This is because the HI specification (for certain scenarios) calls for navigation-style view controller presentation, but WKWebView can't make any guarantees
6853 // about clients' view controller hierarchies, so we can only try our best to avoid presenting modally. Clients can implicitly opt in to specced behavior by using
6854 // UINavigationController to present the web view.
6855 if (_inputNavigationViewControllerForFullScreenInputs)
6856 [_inputNavigationViewControllerForFullScreenInputs pushViewController:_presentedFullScreenInputViewController.get() animated:YES];
6857 else
6858 [presentingViewController presentViewController:_presentedFullScreenInputViewController.get() animated:YES completion:nil];
6859 controller = _presentedFullScreenInputViewController.get();
6860 }
6861
6862#if HAVE(QUICKBOARD_CONTROLLER)
6863 if (_presentedQuickboardController) {
6864 [_presentedQuickboardController present];
6865 controller = [presentingViewController presentedViewController];
6866 }
6867#endif // HAVE(QUICKBOARD_CONTROLLER)
6868
6869 // Presenting a fullscreen input view controller fully obscures the web view. Without taking this token, the web content process will get backgrounded.
6870 _page->process().startBackgroundActivityForFullscreenInput();
6871
6872 // FIXME: PUICQuickboardController does not present its view controller immediately, since it asynchronously
6873 // establishes a connection to QuickboardViewService before presenting the remote view controller.
6874 // Fixing this requires a version of `-[PUICQuickboardController present]` that takes a completion handler.
6875 [presentingViewController.transitionCoordinator animateAlongsideTransition:nil completion:[weakWebView = WeakObjCPtr<WKWebView>(_webView), controller] (id <UIViewControllerTransitionCoordinatorContext>) {
6876 auto strongWebView = weakWebView.get();
6877 id <WKUIDelegatePrivate> uiDelegate = static_cast<id <WKUIDelegatePrivate>>([strongWebView UIDelegate]);
6878 if ([uiDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:didPresentFocusedElementViewController:)])
6879 [uiDelegate _webView:strongWebView.get() didPresentFocusedElementViewController:controller.get()];
6880 }];
6881}
6882
6883- (BOOL)_isPresentingFullScreenInputView
6884{
6885#if HAVE(QUICKBOARD_CONTROLLER)
6886 if (_presentedQuickboardController)
6887 return YES;
6888#endif // HAVE(QUICKBOARD_CONTROLLER)
6889 return _presentedFullScreenInputViewController;
6890}
6891
6892- (void)dismissAllInputViewControllers:(BOOL)animated
6893{
6894 auto navigationController = std::exchange(_inputNavigationViewControllerForFullScreenInputs, nil);
6895
6896 if (!self._isPresentingFullScreenInputView) {
6897 ASSERT(!navigationController);
6898 return;
6899 }
6900
6901 if (auto controller = std::exchange(_presentedFullScreenInputViewController, nil)) {
6902 if ([navigationController viewControllers].lastObject == controller.get())
6903 [navigationController popViewControllerAnimated:animated];
6904 else
6905 [controller dismissViewControllerAnimated:animated completion:nil];
6906
6907 [[controller transitionCoordinator] animateAlongsideTransition:nil completion:[weakWebView = WeakObjCPtr<WKWebView>(_webView), controller] (id <UIViewControllerTransitionCoordinatorContext>) {
6908 auto strongWebView = weakWebView.get();
6909 id <WKUIDelegatePrivate> uiDelegate = static_cast<id <WKUIDelegatePrivate>>([strongWebView UIDelegate]);
6910 if ([uiDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:didDismissFocusedElementViewController:)])
6911 [uiDelegate _webView:strongWebView.get() didDismissFocusedElementViewController:controller.get()];
6912 }];
6913 }
6914
6915#if HAVE(QUICKBOARD_CONTROLLER)
6916 if (auto controller = std::exchange(_presentedQuickboardController, nil)) {
6917 auto presentedViewController = retainPtr([controller quickboardPresentingViewController].presentedViewController);
6918 [controller dismissWithCompletion:[weakWebView = WeakObjCPtr<WKWebView>(_webView), presentedViewController] {
6919 auto strongWebView = weakWebView.get();
6920 id <WKUIDelegatePrivate> uiDelegate = static_cast<id <WKUIDelegatePrivate>>([strongWebView UIDelegate]);
6921 if ([uiDelegate respondsToSelector:@selector(_webView:didDismissFocusedElementViewController:)])
6922 [uiDelegate _webView:strongWebView.get() didDismissFocusedElementViewController:presentedViewController.get()];
6923 }];
6924 }
6925#endif // HAVE(QUICKBOARD_CONTROLLER)
6926
6927 if (_shouldRestoreFirstResponderStatusAfterLosingFocus) {
6928 _shouldRestoreFirstResponderStatusAfterLosingFocus = NO;
6929 if (!self.isFirstResponder)
6930 [self becomeFirstResponder];
6931 }
6932
6933 _page->process().endBackgroundActivityForFullscreenInput();
6934}

6985- (NSString *)actionNameForFocusedFormControlView:(WKFocusedFormControlView *)view
6986{
6987 if (_focusedElementInformation.formAction.isEmpty())
6988 return nil;
6989
6990 switch (_focusedElementInformation.elementType) {
6991 case WebKit::InputType::Select:
6992 case WebKit::InputType::Time:
6993 case WebKit::InputType::Date:
6994#if ENABLE(INPUT_TYPE_COLOR)
6995 case WebKit::InputType::Color:
6996#endif
6997 return nil;
6998 case WebKit::InputType::Search:
6999 return WebCore::formControlSearchButtonTitle();
7000 default:
7001 return WebCore::formControlGoButtonTitle();
7002 }
7003}

7048- (NSString *)selectMenu:(WKSelectMenuListViewController *)selectMenu displayTextForItemAtIndex:(NSUInteger)index
7049{
7050 auto& options = self.focusedSelectElementOptions;
7051 if (index >= options.size()) {
7052 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
7053 return @"";
7054 }
7055
7056 return options[index].text;
7057}
7058
7059- (void)selectMenu:(WKSelectMenuListViewController *)selectMenu didCheckItemAtIndex:(NSUInteger)index checked:(BOOL)checked
7060{
7061 ASSERT(_focusedElementInformation.isMultiSelect);
7062 if (index >= self.focusedSelectElementOptions.size()) {
7063 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
7064 return;
7065 }
7066
7067 auto& option = self.focusedSelectElementOptions[index];
7068 if (option.isSelected == checked) {
7069 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
7070 return;
7071 }
7072
7073 _page->setFocusedElementSelectedIndex(index, true);
7074 option.isSelected = checked;
7075}

7083{
7084 if (index >= self.focusedSelectElementOptions.size()) {
7085 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
7086 return NO;
7087 }
7088
7089 return self.focusedSelectElementOptions[index].isSelected;
7090}
